title: butterflies
directions: Put 2 egg roll skins together.
Cut into thirds.
(Each third makes one butterfly or bow.)
Seal both ends together with water. Cut a 1 1/2-inch slit in the center of each egg roll skin.
Fold skin back and around through the slit to form loose "bow" or "butterfly" shape.
Heat oil to 375°.
Deep fry skins to a golden brown color.
Drain on paper towel. Sift powdered sugar or drizzle Karo syrup or light corn syrup over skins.

title: finger cheesewiches
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature and mix.
Remove crust from bread.
Spread cheese mixture on 3 slices and place them together, then cut into 3 strips and cut these 3 strips in half (end up with 6 pieces).
Frost sides and top with cheese mixture thinly.
Place cubes on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put into plastic bag and keep frozen.

title: easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 6 mini loaf pans and 4 (6-inch) loaf pans.

title: scrumptious ice cream torte
directions: Crush Heath bars. Soften ice cream. Split ladyfingers in half and line the bottom and sides of a 10 or 12-inch spring-form pan. Spoon layer of chocolate ice cream over ladyfingers. Cover with half of crushed Heath bars. Add layer of vanilla ice cream.
Cover with remaining Heath bars. Add top layer of peppermint ice cream. Freeze at least 8 hours.
Unmold and top with sweetened whipped cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mrs. sullivan's coffee cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, sugars, nutmeg, salt and oil.
Set aside 3/4 cup.
Continue, adding buttermilk, soda and egg.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
To reserved flour mixture, add the nuts and cinnamon to make streusel topping. Sprinkle topping over cake and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: *I always bake my pie shell some before adding filling, but do not brown them.

title: aunt bill's candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans, in 4 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Mix well.
Microwave on Roast for 15 minutes.
Mix well.
Microwave on Roast for 13 to 15 minutes longer to soft ball stage or 236° on candy thermometer.
Stir in vanilla. Beat until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate zucchini sheet cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Beat well.
Sift flour and rest of dry ingredients together.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes on top shelf of oven.
Check before 45 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese cornbread
directions: Heat cornmeal and 1 1/4 cups milk over medium heat until thick and dry, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes.
Spoon cornmeal mixture into a bowl.
Add remaining milk, butter and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in salt, baking powder and red chiles.
Stir in cheese and bacon.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until cooked through.

title: microwave jelly
directions: In 2 quart microwave bowl, put sugar and juice.
Stir well. Add lemon juice and stir.
Put in microwave for 10 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell and stir well.
Put back in microwave and let boil 2 minutes.
Makes 2 pints.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tennessee chip salad
directions: Stir Jell-O until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 mixture into oblong Pyrex dish and chill until firm, then spread 1 cup sour cream over it.
Pour remaining Jell-O over and chill until firm.

title: our soup
directions: Combine ingredients in large pot.
Cook for about 2 hours.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator two hours.
Serve.

title: french cookies
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar.
Then flour and vanilla.
Use 6 eggs first.
After all is combined if batter is too thick add other 2 eggs.
Spoon batter by tablespoon and bake in a waffle iron, until lightly browned.
All depends on size of waffle iron--you can make 1 big one or smaller ones at same time.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix.
Serve cold with potato chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Marinate meat (chicken, beef or ribs) 1 hour.
Can be marinated overnight.
Baste meat with sauce while broiling.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread, cut in quarters and place in bottom of 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage.
Drain and crumble the sausage.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Cover sausage with Cheddar cheese.
Mix together the eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix cottage cheese, 2 cups shredded Mozzarella and 1 egg. Drain and squeeze defrosted spinach; add salt, oregano and pepper. In greased 9 x 12-inch dish, spread small amount of sauce, later 1/3 noodles, 1/3 cheese mixture, 1/3 cheese slices and 1/3 sauce. Repeat 2 times more.
Sprinkle with remaining shredded Mozzarella. Pour water around edges.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Remove foil and serve.

title: barb's cream filling
directions: Drain pineapple or mandarin oranges, chopped, leaving just a little juice.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together for approximately 1 minute at medium speed.
Add pineapple and blend about 3 minutes at high speed.

title: pork-n-bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook for about 30 minutes on medium heat.
Serve.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Gently mix cauliflower.
Pour into greased baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Put carrots, celery, onion, water and bouillon cubes in saucepan and cook until tender.
Cook milk, flour and cheese over low heat until smooth; pour into vegetables and simmer until thoroughly blended.

title: sam houston white cakedallas, texas
directions: Bake in lightly greased 9 X 12-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.

title: beef roast with mushroom and onion soup
directions: Line a pan with a large piece of foil.
Sprinkle onion soup mix in bottom of pan.
Lay roast on top of dry soup mix.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over top of roast. Fold foil loosely over top of roast.
Cook in oven at 325° about 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Add milk, baking powder, salt and vanilla and beat in. Add flour a little at a time beating until smooth.
Then add poppy seed, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: cracker spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and soup until blended.
Stir in onions and dried beef.
Refrigerate.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Pour all ingredients, except sherbet, in large punch bowl. Add scoop of sherbet.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain. In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and sage. Combine milk, bouillon and water.
Slowly pour into saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken, pimiento and parsley. Spoon into 6 individual casseroles.
Roll and cut pastry into circles 1 inch smaller than top of casseroles.
Place atop filling.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until the crust is lightly browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: summer tea
directions: Make the tea. Add both concentrates and stir. Serve in clear pitcher with ice cubes.

title: graham bread
directions: Thicken water with flour to a thin batter.
Add sugar, salt and yeast and stir in more flour until quite stiff.
In the morning, add a small teaspoon soda and flour enough to make the batter stiff as can be stirred with a spoon.
Put into pans and let rise again, then bake in even oven, not too hot at first (keep warm while rising).
Smooth over the loaves with a spoon or knife dipped in water.

title: jerrie's sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If not moist enough to stick together, add water, a tablespoon at a time.
Roll into small balls (about 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Drain on paper towels.
May be frozen, warmed and served. Best when served hot.

title: guava chicken
directions: Put chicken in bowl, layer of onions, layer of chicken, etc. until used up.
Heat the jelly and ketchup until jelly melts; add lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand overnight.
Bake skin down 1/2 hour, turn and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes; cut thin slice from bottom of each tomato to prevent tipping.
Remove pulp from each tomato, leaving a 1/2-inch wall; chop enough pulp to make 1/3 cup.
Mix tomato pulp, green pepper, cheese, croutons and salt.
Fill tomatoes.
Place in ungreased oblong baking dish.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until tomatoes are heated through.
Garnish with parsley sprigs or crumbled, crisply fried bacon, if desired.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Combine remaining ingredients with spinach; mix well.
Chill mixture for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Form spinach mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: rice waffles
directions: If using fresh cook them till tender. Canned ones drain most of the liquid away an place in kettle add butter and sugars. Cook on medium heat till all is melted and stir well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add 1/2 pkg. taco seasoning mix.
Set aside to cool.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Gently mix in meat.
Combine dressing, mayonnaise, ketchup and remaining taco seasoning in a bowl to make dressing.
Pour over salad and toss.
Makes 10-12 servings.

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add to liquid mix the sugar, nutmeg, flour and baking powder.
Combine these dry ingredients and mix before adding to liquid mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon (approximately) into grease (approximately 375°).
Fry until well browned for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Cool.
If desired, add sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
I put them in plastic bags to do this.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg and buttermilk; beat until smooth. Grease baking pan or heat pan first.
Bake at 350° for until brown.

title: jello dessert
directions: Pour jello into hot water.
Mix thoroughly then cool for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Mix well and pour into an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.
To make the topping: mix the cream cheese, marshmallows and whipping cream together. Cover and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
The next day, whip the cream cheese mixture until well blended.
Pour over jello. Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill. Serve.

title: natchez plantation tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and tea is ready to serve.
Serve cool or hot.
Place sliced oranges and lemons on top for color.
Keep in refrigerator.
Serves 20.

title: devil dogs
directions: Put everything in bowl and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Cook Duncan Hines butter cake mix according to directions. Let cool. Punch holes in cooled cake. Mix crushed pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil, then simmer about 5 minutes. Pour over cooled cake when cooled. Mix oleo, cream cheese, chopped pecans and confectioners sugar. Spread this on cooled cake.

title: shrimp and fish creole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in margarine until tender. Add tomatoes, parsley, paprika, sugar, cayenne and bay leaf. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add fish to sauce, then add shrimp. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until shrimp turns pink and fish flakes easily with fork. Blend together cornstarch and water. Add to creole and cook, stirring until slightly thickened.

title: broiled quail
directions: Split cleaned birds down back.
Rub with olive oil, butter and salt and pepper.
Place 2 inches under preheated broiler for 8 minutes; basting again with olive oil.
Serve on buttered toast with mushrooms.
Allow 1 quail per person.

title: avocado salza
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except avocado. Store in sealed container at room temperature for 6 to 8 hours. Before serving, add diced avocados.
Serve with chicken or your favorite grilled meat.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it. Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 3-inch strip of aluminum foil.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking. Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until soft.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and ham.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature. Makes approximately 2 quarts.

title: chocolate cherry ice cream
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in egg yolks with 2 cups of cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very hot.
Do not boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in remaining cream, almond and vanilla extracts.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer instructions.
Immediately fold in cherries and almonds.

title: halibut with wine and lemon
directions: Arrange the fish fillets in a single layer and close together in a shallow pan.
Beat together egg, 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1/2 cup of the wine, salt and pepper and pour over the fish.
Cover and chill for about 1 hour.
Lift fish from marinade, draining.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the butter in a wide frying pan; add fish fillets and brown on both sides.
Place fish on a heated platter in a warm place.
In a pan, melt the remaining butter; add 1/8 cup of the marinade, the remaining lemon juice and wine. Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour some of the sauce over fish and pass the remainder to add to each serving.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 2.

title: german pancake
directions: Melt margarine in ovenproof skillet, about 10 minutes in diameter.
Combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg in bowl.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and lemon juice and serve immediately.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl; mix until softened.
Add egg and onion; mix well.
Heat water to boil.
Add beef bouillon; let dissolve.
When water is slightly cooled, add to cream cheese mixture and blend together.
Remember, the water should not be too hot, or it will cook the egg.
You don't want that to happen. Thaw spinach; squeeze out excess water.
Add spinach to cream cheese; mix well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Put spinach in casserole.
Bake, covered, for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lazy man's cabbage rolls
directions: Saute meat, onions, pepper and garlic.
Mix with rice and cabbage.
Put in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 can tomato soup and 1 cup tomato juice or sauce and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes, covered.
Serves 8.

title: meat-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger (you may add onion if preferred).
While browning meat, cook macaroni and drain.
Add soup, cheese and mushrooms to hamburger mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
(This is a great dish to make 3 or 4 of and store in freezer for baking later.
Great, especially when you work and have little time to get dinner.)

title: enchiladas
directions: Boil together in saucepan the enchilada mix, tomato sauce and water.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup of sauce to meat.
Also add 1/2 cup Mozzarella and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese to meat.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour enough sauce to cover the bottom.
Dip tortilla shells into sauce and fill with 3 tablespoons of meat mixture, placing them seam down.
Pour remaining sauce over prepared enchiladas and remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and garnish with lettuce, tomato and sour cream before serving.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine the flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut the shortening into the flour mixture with a pastry blender.
Add the milk; stir thoroughly with a fork.
Turn mixture out onto a floured board; roll or put to desired thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake in any kind of pan at 300° about 1/2 hour.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream shortening until soft and smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and jam. Add buttermilk and mix into batter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs 1 at a time beating well after each addition.
Add crushed wafers alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans, and mix well.
Pour into a large greased tube or bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil and leave on cabinet for 3-4 days, or put in freezer.
(Do not cut right away because it will be dry and tasteless.)

title: extract pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter, oleo and sugar until fluffy. Alternately add milk, eggs and flour, beating well after each addition.
Add extract.
Bake for 2 hours in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Start in cold oven, then turn to 325°.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted oleo or butter over top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.
When cool, top with whipped cream.

title: crescent roll - cheese cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
On a slightly greased cookie sheet, spread one can crescent rolls.
Pinching together at all seams.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of rolls.
Take second can of rolls and put on top of cream cheese layer.
Pinch together all seams.
Beat the egg white until foamy; brush the top of the rolls with it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix together, eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Then mix with dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in a tube or loaf pan for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates, baking soda and butter into boiling water.
Stir and let cool.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix all ingredients.
Fill bread pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: sunday entree
directions: Pan-fry pork chops or steaks in water.
Cook until tender. Before meat is half done, toss in a few cauliflower and broccoli flowerets.
Cover and finish cooking meat.
Add only enough water to not scorch.
Turn down heat.
Add chopped bell pepper with flowerets, if you like.
Open up a can of chicken and dumplings. Spoon onto skillet mixture and heat without lid.
Be sure water is almost cooked away before adding dumplings.
Can be served from frying pan or pour into Pyrex dish, spooning meat over into dish first.
Finish in 325° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes to set and brown around edge of dish.
Serve with salad and sliced tomatoes.

title: stir and roll pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix flour and salt.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into a measuring cup (don't stir).
Add all at once to flour.
Stir until mixed.
Press into balls.
Smooth and flatten slightly.
Roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Press into pie pans.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Put cream of mushroom soup in a casserole dish; add a little water for moistness.
Alternate layers of hamburger, sliced (thin) onion and potatoes and finally pour Cheddar cheese soup on top (add a little water).
Put lid on dish and bake in a preheated oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Boil zucchini in water until tender.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk until firm.
Mix pudding and cheese mixtures together with a whisk.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Starting with crushed cookies, alternately layer cookies and Cool Whip mixture in pot, ending with crumbs.
Arrange worms on top of "dirt."
Insert flower into center of pot.
You can put worms in between each layer.
Chill before serving.

title: mommy's easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done then chop.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Add chicken, tomatoes, soup and cheez whiz.
Stir until cheez whiz is completely melted and all ingredients are thoroughly mixed together.

title: haystacks
directions: Line large cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In double boiler top over hot, not boiling, water, melt butterscotch pieces with salad oil, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl, mix chow mein noodles and marshmallows.
Pour on butterscotch; mix well with fork.
Onto cookie sheet, drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls (if mixture thickens, place over hot water a few minutes). Refrigerate until set.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add oil, carrots and eggs.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour in lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting or your favorite kind.

title: egg nest
directions: Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Remove crusts from bread.
Place 1 slice of bread in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Drop a raw egg into each cup.
Top each with 1/4 teaspoon butter. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until eggs are cooked and bread is toasted.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add yolks and enough milk to form smooth mixture.
Stir in rest of milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and raisins (including juice).
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir nuts into flour mixture.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Combine well and stir in apples.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread batter evenly in the prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apricot-lemon warmer
directions: In medium saucepan, combine apricot nectar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Add cinnamon (if desired).
Bring just to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and discard the stick.
Stir in Equal until dissolved.
May be garnished with lemon slice and cinnamon stick.
Makes 5 (6 ounce) servings.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 1/2 Fruit.

title: cherry cheese torte
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar in pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put over top of potatoes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together.
Right before serving, pour mixture over cut/torn lettuce, shredded Cheddar cheese and crushed nacho or plain tortilla chips in large bowl and toss, adding more dressing if necessary.

title: ooey gooey treats
directions: Mix all ingredients well and press in a 9 x 12 pan.

title: rice with lamb sauce(riz bi yahkna)
directions: In saucepan, brown meat and onion in oil.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Let cook over med. heat till meat is cooked through and sauce thickens a bit. Meanwhile in another saucepan, melt butter and add rosemarino.
Stir constantly till golden brown.
Add rice and water to cover all.
Cover and slowly boil till water is absorbed and rice is cooked.
In a frying pan, brown onion in oleo.
When rice is cooked, add onion mixture to rice. Serve sauce over rice.

title: potato and shrimp soup
directions: In heavy 4-quart pan saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until limp; add green onions, potatoes, salt and water.
Bring to a boil and then simmer partially covered for 45 minutes or until potatoes are very tender.
Mash.
Add shrimp and cook 20 to 30 minutes until shrimp are done.
Cool.
Add 1/4 cup butter, cream and chives. Adjust seasoning.
Heat through, but do not boil or cream will curdle.

title: low-fat chocolate eclair
directions: Pour milk into a large mixing bowl.
Add dry pudding mix and beat for 1 to 2 minutes until pudding starts to thicken.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Fill paper cups in pans 1/2 to 2/3 full.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix yogurt and cottage cheese, stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill for 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve as a dip for crackers, chips or raw vegetable pieces or serve as dressing for green salad.

title: modeling dough
directions: Mix ingredients in pan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes doughy in consistency. Knead until cool.
Ready for play.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients and pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese and macaroni chili
directions: In saucepan, heat oil and saute onions, green pepper and celery.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and simmer uncovered about 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and uncooked macaroni.
Simmer another 12 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently, or until macaroni is tender.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with mixture of 1/4 cup of flour, salt and pepper. In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown meat in oil.
Stir in 2 cups of water, tomato sauce, bouillon cubes, celery and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cover.
Simmer an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: nutty shake
directions: Blend vanilla ice cream, chocolate syrup and peanut butter. Add milk.
Beat until frothy.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: For sauce, in a small saucepan, stir together the tomato sauce, onion, brown sugar, tomato paste, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, garlic and if desired, hot pepper sauce. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until desired consistency, stirring occasionally. Remove half of the sauce (about 1/2 cup).
Cover and store in the refrigerator for another use for up to 2 weeks.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, onions, mushrooms, peppers, tomatoes, etc.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend well. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix to creamed mixture.
Mix on low speed until just blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: in a hurry?  potato dish
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Add mushroom soup in hot potatoes.
Stir.
Add dash of Greek seasoning or salt and pepper.

title: ginger-raz freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 cups (serving size:
1 cup).

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook sausage, ham, onion, green peppers and garlic in oil until sausage is brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except shrimp, parsley and Tabasco sauce. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook uncovered 5 to 8 minutes longer or until liquid is almost absorbed.
Garnish with parsley and serve with hot sauce, if desired.

title: sugar cookies 2
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then mix in salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Gradually add flour so it is well blended. Drop dough on cookie sheet by spoonful.
Grease bottom of small glass and dip in sugar before pressing down each cookie gently. Add chocolate chips or M&M's, if desired. Bake 8 to 10 minutes (until golden brown on the edges) at 375°.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Brown meat and drain well. Break into small pieces.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been well-greased. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Put rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Place chicken parts over rice.
Mix soup and juice; pour over chicken. Sprinkle soup mix on top; cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into crust. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: easy mexican casserole(can be made ahead of time)
directions: Prepare 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and cooked spinach.
Combine soup, sour cream and garlic salt; set aside.

title: drain opener or cleaner
directions: Pour each in drain in order given.
Rinse with lots of very hot water.
Let faucet run for 15 minutes.

title: franciscan sandwiches
directions: Combine the olive salad ingredients.
Toss to blend.
Let marinate about half an hour at room temperature, if possible. Slice the rolls.
Brush with olive oil. Layer with the cheese, ham and salami.
Top with the olive salad.
Replace top of the roll. Serve or wrap for a bag lunch or picnic.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Cook sugar, egg and pineapple juice together and pour over cool jello.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese and top.

title: frozen strawberry mile high pie
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice at high speed for 15 minutes in large bowl.
Fold in whipped cream and pat mixture in baked pie shell and freeze until serving.

title: macaroni and cheese in a crock-pot
directions: Toss together macaroni and oil.
Grease crock-pot.
Stir all ingredients together.
Place in crock-pot.
Either place on high for 3 hours or place on low for 7 hours.

title: fruit spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add rest of ingredients. Serve with crackers.
Freezes well.

title: can't believe it's a brownie
directions: In saucepan, melt caramels and 1/2 can milk; set aside and keep warm.
Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1/2 can milk until moistened.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread half of this mixture in a well-greased, floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Cool briefly.
Spread chocolate chips evenly over baked cake.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Put remaining cake mixture over top.
Bake for 14 to 18 minutes, until top is set.
Brownie will pull away from sides.
Do not overbake.
Cool; cut into small squares.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Make jello according to package directions.
Add dissolved gelatin and refrigerate until it congeals.
Fold in mayonnaise and all other ingredients.
Beat with Mixmaster to blend.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: aunt pee wee's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender and take meat off bones.
Saute celery and onions in oil until tender.
Add flour, one spoon at a time, to the onions and celery and blend.
Add salt, pepper and margarine.
Add chicken broth, stirring to blend, then add soup.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with Pinwheels.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: crock-pot barbecue(low-fat)
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Turn heat on low.
Cook 14 to 16 hours.
Remove roast and cool.
Break meat into pieces; remove all fat.
Pour juices from crock-pot and discard.
Place meat in layers back in pot.

title: crescent cheese squares
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan with 1 package of crescent rolls.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until very smooth. Spread mixture evenly into pan.
Top with second package of crescent rolls.
Melt butter and pour over entire pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 325° until medium brown. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: delicious holiday dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat pumpkin, milk, sugars, eggs and spices together.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with cake mix.
Pour melted margarine on top; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of dessert comes out clean.
Top with whipped topping.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: In a skillet, brown beef cubes in oil.
Transfer to covered baking dish.
Pour wine into skillet. Scrape up brown bits and pour over beef.
Add seasonings, tomato paste and broth to meat. Cover and bring to a boil.
Transfer to baking dish. Bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove beef. Make a roux of flour and 2 tablespoons butter. Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter. Add to first mixture along with beef and onions.
Mix well.
Serve over rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour; cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook and stir until thick, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, cream and seasonings.
Add vegetables; cook until good and hot.

title: buttered noodles
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In saucepan over low heat, add remaining ingredients.
Heat until butter is melted; stir in hot pasta.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and salsa.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with tortilla chips, cheese and onion; top with spoonful of sour cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch diameter flowerpot, a small hand shovel and artificial flowers.
Plug holes of flowerpot.
Grease inside of flowerpot with margarine.

title: chewy homemade breadsticks(appetizer)
directions: In a large mixer bowl, sprinkle yeast over the 1/4 cup water. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in salad oil, sugar, salt, milk and 2 cups flour.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes or until dough pulls from side of bowl in stretchy strands.
Stir in more flour (about 1 cup) to form a stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth.
Turn dough over into a lightly greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled.
Turn dough out onto board. Knead to expel trapped air.
Cut into 12 equal pieces.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.

title: unusual cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the hot water.
Drain the thawed frozen strawberries and pineapple and add water to make 1 cup liquid and add to gelatin.
Chill the gelatin until it begins to congeal, then add the berries, crushed pineapple, cranberry sauce and the diced marshmallows.
Return to refrigerator until congealed. Serve on lettuce with a little mayonnaise.

title: snowball cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple, coconut and pecan pieces.
Break, but don't crush wafers and layer with mixture in large loaf cake pan.
Top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and crushed nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fig cookies
directions: Cream the butter with brown sugar.
Add eggs, soda (dissolved in sour cream), the cinnamon and figs.
Add flour.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Turn into greased casserole.
Top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 12.

title: creamy sweet corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, heat vegetable oil or butter until melted. Add onion and cook, stirring, over medium-low heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add 2 cup corn kernels, potatoes, chicken broth and bay leaf.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Cool slightly; transfer to a food processor with metal blade and puree in batches if necessary.
Press mixture through a sieve set over the saucepan. Pour milk through the sieve.
Add remaining 1/2 cup corn to the saucepan.
Heat over low heat, stirring until warm; do not boil.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 c. boiling water; onion.
Let set partially, then fold in rest of ingredients and chill.
When set, unmold and serve on a bed of lettuce trimmed with either radish roses or carrot curls.

title: chicken dumplings(instant)
directions: Bring broth and chicken to a rolling boil.
Add thumb-sized pieces of biscuit dough slowly; allow ample time to cook.
If prefer chicken soup, then use only 6 biscuits.

title: no oil chiffon cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks well.
Beating is very important. Add water to egg yolks; beat until light.
Add sugar; beat until creamy or until you can not feel the grain of the sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold egg whites into cake batter; do not stir too much.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Invert cake pan; let cool before removing from pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and jello until thick.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour in baked pie crust.
When cold, top with whipped cream.

title: veal scallopini marsala
directions: Pound veal cutlet with rough side of mallet.
Place in wax paper and pound with flat side of mallet.
Cut into 4 pieces (or get butcher to slice as many thin veal fillets as needed).
Salt, pepper and flour veal.
Saute veal in skillet with olive oil, 2 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, saute onion, garlic, bay leaf, parsley, mushrooms and oregano for 5 minutes. Add wine, chicken stock and Kitchen Bouquet; bring to a boil.
Add veal.
Cover pan and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until veal is tender. Thicken sauce with cornstarch or Buerre Manie.
When sauce thickens, sprinkle with parsley and oregano.
Serve.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in 8 x 8 square pan. Cover with onion and beef soup. Dot with margarine. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: auntie's spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions; pour off grease (or blot with paper towels). Add other ingredients and cook until warm. Serve over spaghetti.

title: broccoli-rice quiche
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Add broccoli and onion; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Drain well and set aside.

title: mamaw ruby's	ketchup
directions: Boil down until thick.	Put into jars and seal.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put sugar over rhubarb and let set overnight.
Cook over low heat until soft.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Mix well until Kool-Aid and Jell-O is dissolved.

title: pennsylvania-dutch lettuce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Combine remaining ingredients except the lettuce; add to bacon.
Heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Tear lettuce into bowl.
Pour hot dressing over lettuce and toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Season with salt, pepper, chopped onion and garlic salt; drain fat. Add soup and tomatoes; let simmer. Layer tortillas, meat mixture and grated cheese in baking dish. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep-dish fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl mix prepared fruit with 1 cup sugar, set aside.
Place butter in a 2-quart baking dish; place in oven until butter melts.
Remove from oven, set aside.
Meanwhile in a medium bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar with flour and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter in baking dish, do not stir.
Spoon prepared fruit over top of batter.
Bake uncovered for 50-60 minutes.
Batter will rise to the top, brown and crisp.
Yields: Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and cocoa. Add other ingredients. Cook until thickens.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: southern praline bars
directions: Melt shortening in 2-quart saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, except frosting, and mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan on rack.
Spread with Praline Frosting.
When cool, cut into bars.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chili ala ono
directions: Brown bacon; add vegetables and cook for 3
minutes.
Add hamburger and cook.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Cook for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, add beans with sauce and cook another 5 minutes.

title: rhubarb orange jam
directions: Bring to a boil and stir constantly 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal or cover with paraffin.

title: cooked pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together, then add egg, lemon juice and juice drained from pineapple.
Mix together and cook over low heat until real thick, stirring all the time to keep from sticking.
Let cool, then add the crushed pineapple and mayonnaise to spread.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Hull, wash and mash the berries.
Add the sugar.
Stir up real well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Put on stove.
Bring to a full rolling boil, one that can't be stirred down.
Stir occasionally before it comes to a hard boil.
Add the Certo, stirring constantly.
Boil real hard for 1 minute.
Remove from stove. Stir and remove any foam, then pour into hot jars and seal immediately.
Fill jars 1/8-inch from the top.

title: english custard bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut buttered bread lengthwise into 3 pieces.
Scald milk (heat to almost boiling) and pour over the beaten eggs which have been mixed with sugar and vanilla.
Add cinnamon.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to
Cut
stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop enough stems
for 1/3 cup.	Saute chopped mushroom stems, onion and green pepper in margarine until tender, approximately 5 minutes.
Remove
from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, thyme, turmeric and
pepper.
Heat margarine in shallow baking dish until melted.
Fill
mushroom caps with stuffing mixture. Place mushrooms, filled
sides
up,
in
baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to top rack of the oven.
Set	to broil or 550° for 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 1 gallon ice cream bucket.
Finish filling bucket with whole milk.
Freeze for about 30 minutes or until freezer stops.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Mix sugar, flour and 1/3 cup of reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple and mix well. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Mix Cheez-Its with melted margarine; sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ground beef one dish meal
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and green pepper.
Cook until onion and green pepper are done.
Add tomato soup, dried noodles and sour cream; cover and simmer.
When noodles are done, add Velveeta cheese on top.

title: no fat dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll.
Cut with tea cake cutter.
Mash with fork.
Bake on 325° until edges begin to brown.

title: layered chocolate pie
directions: Cut butter into flour, using fork or pastry cutter.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and spread evenly in bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen black bottom pie
directions: Pour 3/4 cup of the chocolate sauce into chocolate crumb crust, spreading lightly to cover bottom and sides of crust. Refrigerate until set.
Fill crust with ice cream.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before ready to serve.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup chocolate sauce.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers paper thin, leaving peel on.
Slice onions into thin rings.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables; put about 2 quarts crushed ice on top.
It is the ice and salt that gives an almost brittle, crisp pickle.
Let stand 3 hours, weighted with a plate; drain.

title: dreamsicle punch
directions: Put concentrate, rum (use O.J. can for measure) and vanilla in a large container, an old water jug works well.
Shake well until ingredients are mixed.
Place in the freezer until it becomes slushy.
Once slushy, add ice and shake again until mixed. Slowly add the cream soda.
Agitate the container a few times to mix. Do not shake hard.

title: apple delight
directions: Combine water and vanilla; set aside.
Grease large, glass baking dish.
Add apples; sprinkle with cinnamon, and then pour water mixture over top.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into sugar and flour. Cover apples evenly with this mixture, then bake in a 350° oven for approximately 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Serves four.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock.
Cook green pepper and celery in stock.
Mix chicken, green pepper, mushrooms, pimentos and spaghetti.
Pour in soup (add water, if needed). Place in lightly greased casserole dish and bake in moderate oven until bubbles.
Top with grated cheese and continue baking until cheese melts.
Total Baking Time:
30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: calico bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 12 hours.
Drain beans; add 8 cups water and ham hocks.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, onions, carrots, chili powder, salt, pepper and lemon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes. Remove bones from soup; cut meat from bones.
Return meat to soup. Remove and discard lemon slice.
Makes 10 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat, draining off and discarding fat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 3 noodles (the noodles won't quite fill the bottom).
Just space them evenly and they will expand to fill gaps. Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Top with 1/3 of the cheese mixture, mashing it with your fingers or a fork to spread it around the noodles.
It won't be even, but that's okay.
Top with 1/3 of the sauce.
Next layer:
3 noodles, cottage cheese, meat and sauce. Top layer:
3 noodles, cottage cheese, rest of sauce, 8 ounces grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cover the dish tightly with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 1/2 minute or until melted.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Layer half of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Repeat the layers.
Cover and cook on High 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese and spices.
Mix well.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken wings in butter, then into coating.
Arrange chicken wings in lightly oiled ovenproof baking dish.
Bake chicken wings at 375° for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown and done.
Chicken wings should be tender.

title: apple fritters(breakfast)
directions: Make pancakes according to the directions on the box.
Add chopped apples and fry until brown.
Remove from frying pan and dip lightly into confectioners sugar and serve.

title: 8 day pickles
directions: Wash and cut up cucumbers.
Put in churn.
Mix salt in 1 gallon water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 days.
Drain off salt water.
Cover with alum water (1 tablespoon to 1 gallon water).
Let stand 1 day.
Drain and cover with ginger water (1 tablespoon ginger to 1 gallon water).
Let stand 1 day.
Drain and rinse cucumbers once and drain well.
Put back in churn.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pickling spice and bring to a boil.
Put over cucumbers.
Let stand 1 day.
Next day, put cucumbers in jars. Boil liquid and pour over pickles.
Seal and store.

title: white chile with salsa verde
directions: Boil chicken 1/2 hour in water, lemon juice and cumin.
Saute garlic, onion and oil.
Add to chicken.
Also add Shoepeg corn, green chiles, cumin, lemon or lime juice and Northern beans.
Cook until heated through.
In bowl, put tortilla chips and chiles over it.
Top with Salsa Verde and Monterey Jack cheese.

title: french bread dip appetizer
directions: Mix all together, tearing apart corned beef.
(This is better if made day before use.)
To serve, carve out center of loaf of Italian bread.
Place dip mixture in empty center.
May use scraps to dip or cut up another loaf to dip.
May also use other kinds of hard crust bread.

title: apple dip
directions: Whip until smooth.
Slice Granny Smith apples; dip in lemon juice to keep from browning.

title: one bowl fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring every minute.
Stir until blended.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Cut into squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop off mushroom stems.
Saute in butter with grated onion. Add cooked and crumbled bacon to stems and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Brush mushroom caps with butter and bake 5 to 8 minutes. Fill caps with cream cheese mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Broil until golden brown.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook seashells for 10 minutes or 3/4 of the way done.
Brown ground meat; add onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Mix egg with cottage cheese; add to the ground meat and a little Parmesan cheese.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 11 x 8-inch baking pan with shortening.
Stir the corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl until mixed.
Beat in milk, oil and eggs.
Beat by hand.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Boil turkey giblets until done.
Boil eggs to hard-boiled stage.
Cut up onions.
In a large bowl, combine stuffing mix, onions, eggs, meat from turkey giblets and salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough juice from turkey giblets to mix ingredients to a thick soupy mix.
Place in baking dish and bake at approximately 400° until set and lightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and pull off bone into pieces.
Break up spaghetti and cook according to package directions, then cool.

title: grandma's quick chick trick
directions: Place chicken pieces in bottom of greased baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Heat and pour over chicken pieces.
Crumble crackers over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Fry hamburg in medium frying pan until cooked.
Cook macaroni according to directions on box; drain.
Add hamburg, Ricotta cheese and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into glass baking dish. Sprinkle pizza cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Mix as package says and pour in 2 round pans.

title: malia's wedding punch
directions: Mix together the jello and hot water to dissolve jello.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cran-strawberry juice and pineapple juice.
Mix.
Add cold water.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and take off bones.
Shred chicken and add tomato sauce, chili and garlic salt to taste.
Heat tortillas on ungreased skillet until warm.
Wrap in tinfoil to keep warm.
Put meat mixture (spoonful) in warm tortilla.
Also spoonful of each grated cheese.
Roll tortillas and line in greased pan.
Top with enchilada sauce and grated cheese.
Heat until enchiladas are heated through and cheese is bubbly at 325°, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: In a large bowl combine 1/2 cup of butter and the cream cheese, and let come to room temperature.
Add 2 cups of flour and blend well.
Chill.
Roll out half of the dough and place in a 9-inch pie pan.
In a saucepan combine the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour the mixture into the crust.
Roll out the remaining crust and place over the filling.
Cut slits in the top crust and allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: fantastic punch(for a large group)
directions: Boil the sugar and the 2 cups water together to make a syrup, about 10 minutes.
Add tea, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Chill several hours.
Add the thawed strawberries and juice, remaining water and ginger ale.
Pour over block of ice or ice cubes.
Serves 75 generously.

title: beef stroganoff sandwich
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Cut bread lengthwise in half; butter both halves and place on baking sheets.
Remove meat mixture from the heat; stir in sour cream.
Spoon onto the bread.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
(Bake longer for crispier bread.)

title: lime jell-o mold
directions: Drain juice from crushed pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: 5 minute chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a medium size saucepan over medium heat.
Heat about 4 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Try this topped with shredded jalapeno Jack cheese and sour cream or plain yogurt.
Good served with cornbread.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix well. Bake in tube pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Cream the peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar until mixture is of consistency to form balls.
Pat out in pan or form into long rolls.
Melt chocolate bits in top of double boiler.
Brush on top of candy in pan or dip logs into chocolate. Place logs on waxed paper to allow to harden.
Place in refrigerator for quicker hardening.
When hard, slice to serve.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350°
for about 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for another 25 minutes.
This makes a crisp top.
Can be frozen.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Heat peaches until hot.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish.
Mix flour and milk.
Pour in greased baking dish. Pour hot peaches on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is done.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Drain and rinse beans, peas and corn. Mix all
together and refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Allow to set.
Combine sugar, lemon juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add whipped topping and spread over top of first mixture.

title: hot cocktail canapes
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with dressing mix.
Fold in cheese and pepper or ham or shrimp.
Mound on 40 bite size cuts of a variety of breads and broil until puffed and browned, about 2 minutes.
Decorate, if desired.

title: cheesy broccoli 'n mushroom baked
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Whip together soup, salad dressing and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scallion dip
directions: In bowl, mix first 3 ingredients well; add olives and mix again.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Remove and roll into ball.
Roll onto chopped nuts.
Place back in fridge for 1/2 hour or so. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine strawberries, oil, eggs and sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and add to strawberry mixture.
Add nuts and
stir until blended.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add to cucumber mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk; add 1/2 cup butter, water, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in 1 cup flour, then add 2 eggs.
Mix in 5 to 6 cups flour; knead for about 15 minutes or use food processor for 7 minutes.
Cover and let raise until double in size, then punch down and let raise for 30 minutes.
On floured surface, roll dough in oblong 14 x 18-inch shape.
Spread evenly with 1/3 cup softened butter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and desired cinnamon. Roll and cut 12 rolls 1 1/4-inches thick.
Prepare a 9 x 12-inch pan by spreading evenly with 1/2 cup softened butter and sprinkling with 3/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon as desired. Place rolls in prepared pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.
Invert pan right out of oven onto parchment paper. Makes 12 rolls.

title: ham and vegetable casserole
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients in large skillet until vegetables are tender.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine salad dressing mix and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir into ham and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley if desired.
Makes 6 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Slightly thaw bread or rolls, enough to spread out on baking dish. Spread amount of sauce you desire on the dough. Add any toppings you like. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, depending on thickness of your crust.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: In large saucepan, stir soup until smooth; blend in milk and cheese.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Just before serving, toss hot noodles with butter; combine with soup mixture.
Serve with additional cheese.

title: ham stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half; remove egg yolks.
Mash up with fork.
Add ham, onion flakes, salt, pepper, curry powder and Miracle Whip to mashed egg yolks.
Blend well.
Take tablespoon and stuff egg whites.
Add olive to top of each half.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Add graham cracker crumbs.
Press down to make crust.
Beat eggs and rest of margarine and confectioners sugar together.
Spread evenly over crust.
Spread pineapple.
Cut bananas over the pineapple and spoon Cool Whip on top.
Add cherries and chocolate syrup (to taste) over the top.
Refrigerate for 5 hours.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix together the Jell-O, pecans, coconut, milk and vanilla. Shape dough into strawberries.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into berry shape balls; roll in sugar crystals.
Tint almonds with green food coloring for garnishing.
Keep in cool place.
Makes 48 strawberries.

title: yugoslavian christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter with 1/2 cup sugar; add egg yolk and salt. Stir in flour. Pat mixture into 10 x 15 inch pan. Stir jelly over dough. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add remaining cup of sugar, beating slowly. Fold in most of nut and the lemon extract. Spread meringue over jelly. Top with the rest of the nuts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In one bowl mix the cream cheese and butter.
Mix in powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Second, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in the cream cheese and pudding mixture.
Pour over cookies.
Put crushed cookies on top.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the jello in with the cream first, then add other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: macho nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread mix in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Drain olives well.
Layer remaining in order listed. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Bring to room temperature and serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Layer ingredients
in a flat casserole dish.
Heat at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: nilla-orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to stiffen.
Roll into balls.
Will freeze.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together strawberries, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into strawberry mixture.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 3 medium or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out dry.
Makes 2 large loaves.
Bread freezes well.

title: shrimp almondine
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse.
Melt margarine; add almond and pepper and brown lightly.
Stir in salt, flour and caraway seed.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Put in spaghetti, shrimp and corn, then Tabasco and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bran 'n raisin molasses muffins
directions: Combine All-Bran, milk and molasses; let stand until most of the moisture is taken up.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add with raisins to first mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased (with Crisco) muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for about 25 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pans.
Yields 12 to 15 muffins, 2 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to directions; drain and place in casserole dish.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Put pats of butter on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour into flour mixture all at once.
Blend only until moistened with spoon.
An easy crust to handle without toughening.
It will keep up to 2 weeks or longer.
Bake at 375° or 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch.

title: nana's turkey stuffing
directions: In saucepan, cook turkey neck.
Cover with water.
Add 1/2 cup celery and onion for about 1 1/2 hours, until neck is cooked.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup celery, onion, apples and walnuts with 1 package stuffing mix.
Take some of the neck meat and add to mixture.
Add water from pan until mixture is moistened.
Add melted butter with sage and poultry seasoning.
Salt and pepper to taste.
May add some stuffing bread, too.

title: lemon refrigerator dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add juice, salt and rind. Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip Milnot until very stiff; gradually beat in sugar, then jello mixture.
Line bottom of 8 x 12-inch dish with vanilla crumbs.
Pour mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: elaine's favorite hamburger patties with gravy
directions: Mix ground beef into patties.
Roll in flour.
Brown in fat on both sides, making sure patties are well browned.
Mix other ingredients in cup.
Pour over meat patties.
Add water.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: quick pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sprinkle yeast from hot roll mix over water in a large mixing bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add flour mixture from hot roll mix, beating well.
Turn out dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes or until smooth. Cover with bowl.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Divide in half and roll each into 12-inch circle.
Fit each circle into 12-inch pizza pan, pressing edges onto side of pan.
Brush with oil.
Spread with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place pans on cookie sheets. Bake pizzas 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Make roux by slowly browning flour in shortening.
When golden brown, add onion, celery, garlic and pepper.
Cook at low heat until vegetables separate from fat.
Brown chicken in some extra shortening, using enough to sear chicken well.
Add chicken to roux mixture and cook together for a few minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour off fat in which chicken was browned, leaving drippings at the bottom.
To this, add water and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken, adding enough extra boiling water to cook the chicken tender and to give gumbo the desired consistency.
Add bay leaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; reserve 2 cups of broth.
Place cut up chicken in 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups plus 1 cup broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix butter and 1 cup broth; stir in stuffing mix. Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender, drain and mash.
Add butter, cheese, beaten egg, onion, milk and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Put into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Cook turkey in small amount of oil.
Drain.
Add small can of chipped chili peppers, soups and tomato sauce.
Cook until well blended and fairly thickened.

title: lynn's spiced turkey
directions: Slice eggplant, onions and peppers.
Chop garlic.
Put all in a roasting pan.
Fill the pan 1/4 full of water.
Add the turkey breast.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Slice turkey and enjoy hot.

title: simple(ly) wonderful biscuits
directions: Mix together in bowl. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour.
In a skillet heat oil and brown chicken on all sides.
Combine rice, poultry, seasonings, salt, pepper, milk and water.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken satay
directions: Cut the chicken breasts on the diagonal into very thin strips and place in a shallow dish.
Combine the marinade ingredients and pour over the chicken. Stir once, cover, and leave to marinate overnight.

title: leila's eggplant salvia
directions: Slice eggplant, onion and tomatoes into very thin slices. Arrange in layers in greased casserole: eggplant, onion and tomatoes (in that order), seasoning lightly between layers. Combine lemon juice and oil; drizzle on top.
The dressing will penetrate, even though it appears scant.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes, basting occasionally with juices that form in the dish.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine in order given.
Mix well and top with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not grease pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to above ingredients with nuts.
Grease and flour bread pan and let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds; put through food grinder.
Use all of the juice. Boil slowly 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the pectin.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Put in small jars.
Makes 5 jars.

title: no fat lo-cal pumpkin muffins
directions: Whisk eggs.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into Pam sprayed 12 tin muffin pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in double boiler.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over hot water until mixture is smooth and thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover and refrigerate until set.

title: special corn bread
directions: Mix by hand or in blender all the ingredients and bake for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: smoked brisket
directions: The brisket is the lowest priced cut and is usually ground into hamburger.
This marinade and slow cooking process tenderizes and adds flavor.
The meat will fall apart in slivers that you can add barbecue sauce and serve on a bun for a delicious sandwich.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Measure and sift dry ingredients together. Cut shortening into mixture. Add milk and yeast. Stir until well blended. Store in refrigerator about 1 hour before baking. Roll dough 1/2-inch. Cut into biscuits. Let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 450° until brown. Yields 24.

title: chocolate bavarian pie
directions: Soften in a 1-qt. saucepan the gelatin in cold water.
Stir in sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir over medium heat until gelatin and sugar dissolve completely, about 5 minutes.
Don't boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 c. Pet milk.
Chill in small bowl until firm.
Beat in with mixture at low speed until mixture is broken up.
Add 2/3 cup Pet milk and the vanilla.
Beat at high speed until mixture fills bowl.
Let stand a few minutes or until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Heap into a graham cracker crust.
Shave a Hershey bar over the top.
Chill.

title: mushroom-rice casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish with the stick of margarine and place the rest of the margarine stick in dish.
Add rest of the ingredients; stir.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
For first 45 minutes, rice will appear raw, but it is always done in an hour.

title: apricot oat muffins
directions: In a small saucepan, heat orange juice until boiling.
Mix in apricots and brown sugar.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Combine oat bran, wheat germ, whole wheat flour and baking powder. Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together oil, skim milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients and apricot/orange juice mixture; mix until just moistened.
Fill greased muffin tin or cupcake papers 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 135 calories per muffin.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Lightly dust raisins with flour.
Add coconut, fruit and nuts and stir well.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla, stirring only until combined.
Spoon batter into cupcake tins and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Muffins should "ripen" for 24 hours for maximum blending of flavors.

title: overnight scalloped chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and cheese in large bowl.
Add chicken, macaroni and eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Toss the bread crumbs with remaining butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate fudge frozen upside-down cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add chopped walnuts. Warm milk and butter together; whisk into dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add melted chocolate; beat well.
Pour into pan and level the top.
Drizzle with sauce.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in small saucepan over medium heat until Equal is dissolved. Remove from heat and cool 30 minutes. Stir together all other ingredients in a large bowl. Gently stir in dressing. Cover and chill up to 8 hours. Serve with slotted spoon. Makes 8 cups.

title: almost a pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Turn on; count slowly to 10.
Turn off.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish add soup, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cheese.
Mix together well.
Add green beans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry frozen salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients. Put in a Pyrex dish and freeze until ready to serve.

title: chocolate crisps(makes about 30 crisps)
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with wax paper.
Melt chocolate in double boiler
over hot, but not boiling water (lowest heat), stirring occasionally.
Let	chocolate
cool for 1 minute and add cereal and marshmallows.
Mix well and add flavoring, nuts and
raisins. Shape
the mixture into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place them on the cookie sheet and put in refrigerator until firm (about 2 or 3 hours).

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate; combine with brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough, then drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll to coat. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ketchup beef stroganov
directions: In a medium glass bowl mix all ingredients together and stir well.
Refrigerate over night.
In a medium skillet, over medium heat cook the marinated meat with juices for about 45 minutes, or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
When almost done, stir in 1 cup of ketchup and let boil about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Serve over
fries.

title: potato lefse
directions: When potatoes are cooked add butter while mashing, then rice. Add the cream, sugar and salt. Cool for about 2 hours in refrigerator. Add the flour. From into balls. Roll thin and bake on lefse griddle. Makes about 12 to 15. Best served with butter, cinnamon and sugar.

title: mom's four bean salad
directions: Mix all beans together and pour sauce over and mix into beans.

title: quick skillet stew and dumplings
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet; pour off excess fat. Add 1 can sauce, vegetables, water, salt, thyme and pepper. Combine well and bring to a boil.

title: speedy tartar sauce
directions: Just mix in blender or shaker and serve over your favorite fish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Arrange bread cubes in greased casserole dish. Beat eggs well; add milk, cream cheese and maple syrup and pour over bread. Let set overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: delicious portabella mushroom
directions: Mix oil, wine, garlic, salt and shallot in a bowl. Pour over sliced mushrooms. Marinate at least 2 hours. Grill or saut mushrooms in a medium-hot skillet with little olive oil.

title: heavenly zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; transfer to a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and smelling wonderful, approximately 45 minutes.

title: winter tea
directions: Put broken cinnamon sticks in a tea ball.
Add everything except tea bags in pot and boil 3 minutes.
Add tea bags and let steep until strong enough for you.

title: chili
directions: When olive oil is hot in a 6-quart pot, add the meat and sear until it is grey.
Add one quart water, cover and cook at simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add all the remaining ingredients, except the flour and cornmeal.
Cook 30 more minutes.
Next, add the flour and meal mixed with one cup water.
Cook 5 minutes more to see if more water is needed for the right consistency.
If there is too much fat, skim off before adding the flour and meal.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bones and break into pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions (1 cup of uncooked rice makes 2 1/2 cups cooked).
Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice.
Add chicken, cheese and rice.
Mix well.
Put in a baking dish sprayed with Pam and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.

title: marinated peas
directions: Boil salad oil, salt, vinegar, pepper, hot water and sugar. Pour over remaining ingredients. Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Fold all ingredients into potatoes, except 1 cup cheese.
Pour into 3-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with reserved cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain well.
