Place in lightly oiled 8 x 8 x 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine soup, cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In small bowl, mix egg, milk and oil.
Pour all at once into oat mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in bacon (crumbled), cheese, green pepper and onion.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: ham-cheese broccoli strata
directions: Lay 8 slices bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese and broccoli with ham.
Cut 4 slices in 1/2 to make triangles and arrange on top.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 55 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cook cantaloupe and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt and egg to cooked cantaloupe, butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool and cover with whipped topping.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy beef and noodles
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in a skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion in drippings until tender; add ground beef and cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings; stir in tomatoes, green pepper, chili sauce, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add noodles and water; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in bacon; sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces and mix together with other ingredients.

title: possin a la nicoise
directions: Coat a baking dish with 1 teaspoon olive oil.
Place fish fillets in a single layer. Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic, parsley and oregano to the mashed tomatoes.
Add wine and mushrooms, if desired. Spread the mixture on the fish and sprinkle the remaining 4 teaspoons olive oil over the fillets.
Dot with bits of
2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, more or less depending on thickness of fish.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini appetizer a la groppuso
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir until well blended.
Fill regular or mini muffin tins half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
May be served hot or cold.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Thirty minutes before serving, preheat broiler.
Remove mushroom stems and finely chop.
Reserve mushroom caps.
In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Cook mushroom stems, onions and next 4 ingredients until onion is tender (about 5 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.

title: fruit and cheese kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice and apple pieces, tossing to coat.
Arrange fruit and cheese onto straws. Yields 12 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Cut fruit into bite size and mix.
Let stand for 2 hours and serve with love.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg and dates.
Cook for 10 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Make into small balls and roll in coconut.
Makes about 50.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, oil and milk to make dough.
Peel and cut apples of choice.
Roll out dough and wrap around apples.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon on the apple before wrapping.
Boil 2 cups sugar, water and butter; pour over dumplings.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Yields 8 to 12.

title: fudge royale
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved and then bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally and cook to 236° or until a small amount of candy dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla but do not stir.
Allow to cool for 15 minutes; then beat until mixture thickens.
Stir in nuts and quickly pour into a buttered 8-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, uncooked rice, onion, celery salt, salt & pepper. Roll into small balls. Place in a greased casserole dish. Pour tomato soup mixture over them. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: moussaka
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Brown eggplant slices in a non-stick frypan.
Set aside.

title: baked potato soup
directions: On medium heat, melt margarine and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring until well mixed.
Add potatoes and green onions; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except for cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup when served.

title: peppernuts
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and shortening in large bowl at high speed until creamy, about 3 minutes.
Turn mixer to low speed. Sift all dry ingredients, except soda, together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk to which soda has been added.
Increase to medium speed 1 to 2 minutes when mixture becomes stiffer.
If possible, allow dough to stand in cool place to stiffen before rolling and cutting.
May decorate with sugars or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: swiss creamed peas
directions: In large saucepan, cook peas according to package directions.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and apples.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Coat chicken.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn again and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: eggplant-crabmeat casserole
directions: Peel, slice or cube eggplant and cook in boiling water with salt added, until tender.
Drain and mash.
Place half of cracker crumbs, butter, onion, celery and crabmeat in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Combine egg and milk.
Pour over contents of casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, soup mix and dried beef and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and serve with crackers.

title: dr.  kuracina's pasta party sauces(for family and friends)
directions: In a food processor with steel blade or blender, place ingredients, except cheese, and process until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: easy cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until it is tender; drain.
Mix cheese soup and milk in a saucepan; bring just to a boil, stirring constantly. Mix well.
Butter glass Pyrex dish.
Arrange broccoli in dish. Pour cheese soup on broccoli.
Make sure broccoli is covered. Place slices of cheese on top of broccoli.
Cook at 350° until bubbly and sliced cheese just starts to brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 3 small individual loaf pans.
Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour into prepared pans. Bake larger loaf pans for 1 hour 20 minutes. Bake small loaf pans approximately 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; mix well. Use as topping on tacos or tossed salad.

title: butter fudge lemon cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Pour wet ingredients into a small bowl; mix with electric mixer on medium for 20 seconds or until smooth.
Pour wet ingredients into dry ingredients.
Continue mixing with electric mixer on medium another 30 seconds or until dough forms.
Make a 1/2 inch ball with your fingers formed around 3 chocolate chips.
Place on a dry cookie sheet in rows 4 across and 6 down.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together except cheese. Pour half batter in greased baking dish. Add half cheese. Add remaining batter. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Dice bacon in small pieces and pan-broil over moderate heat until crisp.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour over salad greens and toss gently until well blended.
Season to taste and serve at once.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Remove seeds from lemons.
Mix lemons with sugar and let stand overnight.
Add beaten eggs and stir.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 375° and bake for 20 minutes.
The Shaker recipe calls for a top crust, but this is optional.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking or roasting pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in covered container.
Yields 5 quarts.
This recipe can be halved.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Mix broccoli, chicken and onion together in a bowl.
Beat milk, eggs, bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour the milk, eggs, etc. over the chicken, broccoli, cheese and onion in greased pie pan.
Bake 25 to 30 min. in 400° oven.
I usually bake it 10-15 min. more in my oven.
The pie will be done when a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: In crock-pot, cook on high for about 3 hours.

title: nutty cracker delights
directions: Place crackers in a single layer in a foil-lined 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add sugar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Add vanilla.
Pour evenly over crackers; sprinkle with nuts.

title: applesauce cake(this is a good breakfast cake.)
directions: Before mixing, sprinkle dates and raisins with some flour, so they don't stick together in mixture.

title: apricot cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add apricots.
Mix in shortening, walnuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 30 minutes more.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: rice and chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix soups and milk
together;
add to rice.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli saute
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, put 1 tablespoon margarine; cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove chicken; keep warm.

title: summertime melon melba
directions: Cut melon in half crosswise and remove seeds.
Slice melon into 1-inch rings.
Remove rind.
Fill each ring with scoops of ice cream.
Top with melted preserves.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling water and cool.
Grease well and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs until thick at high speed.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add oil and cooled chocolate; beat until well blended.
At low speed, add sifted dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add zucchini and nuts with wooden spoon.
Stir until well combined.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until surface springs back when pressed lightly with fingertip.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on rack.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put in saucepan 1/2 cup sugar and let brown; add little water and cook until light syrup (don't let sugar get too brown).
Stir and mix well 1/2 cup sugar, flour or cornstarch, egg yolks and whole egg.
Add to syrup and cook until thick.
Put in baked crust and top with meringue and brown.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Stir in next five ingredients. Beat eggs, oil and vanilla and stir into first mix until just combined.
Fill greased tins.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a 2-quart bowl.
Add in syrup and mix well.
Beat eggs in with fork one at a time.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake near center of 375° oven for about 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Lay meat on chopping board and sprinkle meat with flour mixture.
Pound in flour mixture, turn meat over and repeat.
(This pounding also tenderizes the meat.)
In hot oil in skillet, brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves four people.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix Eagle
Brand milk, confectioners sugar and coconut. Form or shape into
bars
or
balls and chill.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1/3
of
a
block
of
paraffin
in double boiler.
Dip each bar or ball in chocolate mixture.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread bread slices with butter. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Spoon sausage over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper; mix well and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover casserole; refrigerate overnight.

title: roasted loin of pork
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub the sage, cinnamon and cloves over the surface of the pork.
Place it on a rack and roast the pork for 1-1/2 hours or until it registers 160° on a meat thermometer. Let the roast rest for 15 minutes, then slice and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(You can cook bacon to lay on top.)

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Lightly toss the chicken, pineapple, dates, celery and almonds until mixed.
Chill well
before you add the mayonnaise. Serve on crunchy bed of lettuce - serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake one hour at 350°.
Makes 4 (3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch) loaves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry orange bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
In another bowl, combine egg, orange juice, water, butter and orange peel.
Add to dry ingredients just until combined.
Fold in the blueberries.
Pour into a greased and floured 8x4x2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 65-70 minutes or until test done.
Cool for 10 minutes, remove from pan to wire rack.

title: 7-layer mexican dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish in the order listed.
Refrigerate. Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: applesauce cake
directions: After cooking apples stir in soda and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and dry ingredients together.
Use apples for milk.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Grease large casserole.
Add rice, celery, onion, mushrooms, broccoli and parsley.
Heat and mix in a saucepan the remaining ingredients.
Pour the heated sauce into the casserole.
Mix. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft enough to grate.
With your hands, mix sausage with grated cheese, adding Bisquick and baking powder until well mixed.
Then roll into medium size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young, and take only such as have been raised in good moral atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
Or, worse yet, over their heads in debt.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity; keep them warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion.
Serve with 3 good meals a day.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cooking Time: 45 minutes.
Servings: 4 to 6.

title: venison filet - hunter's style
directions: Have steak cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and place in shallow glass dish.
Mix peppercorns, onion, carrot, parsley, thyme, bay leaf, wine and 5 tablespoons olive oil; pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Turn meat in marinade from time to time.
Remove meat from marinade; pat dry.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in skillet; cook venison 3 minutes on each side or depending on desired doneness.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Make sauce in same pan.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Combine spinach, sour cream and soup mix; stir well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over spinach mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandma thelma's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer on stove at least 1 hour.
Serve over pasta.
I also add mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and oregano.

title: beef sirloin tip roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add tomato sauce, water, instant bouillon and pepper; squeeze bag gently to blend ingredients.
Place roast in bag. Peel and quarter vegetables; add to bag.
Turn bag gently to coat ingredients with sauce.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Insert a meat thermometer through slit in the bag into thickest part of the roast.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 3/4 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160°.
Slice roast thinly across the grain.
To serve, spoon gravy from bag over roast and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: springerle
directions: Stir sugar into beaten egg yolks.
Beat whites until stiff, add to egg yolks and sugar.
Stir vigorously for 10 minutes.
Crush ammonium carbonate thoroughly and add to mixture, along with anise oil and lemon rind.
Add flour in several portions, combining well. Divide dough into 3 or 4 portions.
Turn one out onto floured board and place others in refrigerator.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Dust springerle board with flour, by tying flour into a twist of cheesecloth and striking it lightly against the board.
Stamp sheet of dough firmly with the floured springerle board.

title: chicken breast veronique
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts and cut them in half. Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper, tarragon and nutmeg.
Coat chicken in mixture.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water; let cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Beat cream until stiff.
Mix all together and spread over crust.

title: sweet bread (christmas cake)(virgin islands native recipe)
directions: Dissolve yeast cake into 1 cup of warm water.
Add flour enough to make stiff batter.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; beat until smooth.
Cover and set to rise.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add prepared yeast mixture and salt.
Add fruits and beat well.
Sift flour with spices, add alternately with hot milk.
Beat until light.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased tins; allow to rise double in size.
Brush with syrup before and after baking.
(Syrup is made of brown sugar and water.)
Bake at 375°.
The addition of 1/4 cup of cherry cordial or guavaberry liquor gives it the Christmas touch!

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: If using dried peas, add 1 small onion and garlic and 1 quart water.
Bring to a boil, lower flame and let simmer slowly until beans are tender and creamy.
Add cooked rice, stirring gently, until rice is coated with bean mixture.
Add parsley and onion tops.
Chopped ham or bacon may be added to this.

title: chicken with cauliflower and black olives
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil with garlic, salt and pepper to taste over moderate heat in wide, uncovered skillet. While chicken is cooking, blanch cauliflower in boiling water (or microwave). Drain and set aside, but keep warm.
When chicken is brown, add vinegar, rosemary and parsley.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for 3 minutes. Take off cover, turn up heat and boil until vinegar has evaporated.
Add tomatoes and when they begin to boil, add black olives and cauliflower.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes (careful not to overcook cauliflower).
Serve with white rice. Serves 6.

title: herbed green pea soup
directions: In a soup pot, saute the scallions in the oil for 1 minute. Add the thyme and tarragon; saute for another minute.
Stir peas, nutmeg, salt and pepper and hot water.
Cover; bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes, until the peas are tender but still bright green.
Using a slotted spoon, remove about 1 cup of the peas and set aside.
In a blender or food processor, puree the rest of the soup.
Return the pureed soup into the pot; stir in the milk and reserved peas.
Gently reheat, or chill for about 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with scallions, adding croutons if you wish.
Serves 4. Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: In a large skillet, combine tomato sauce, orange juice, onion, raisins, pimiento, oregano, chili powder, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken; return to boiling.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes more or until chicken is tender and no longer pink. Meanwhile, combine cornstarch and water; stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Toss parsley with rice.
Serve chicken mixture over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash navy beans and then run them through hot water until the beans are white again.
Boil slowly 3 1/2 hours in a covered pot containing 4 quarts of water and smoked ham hocks.
Braise onion in a little butter and add it to the soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop vegetables and pepperoni.
Add to cold spaghetti; add spice.
Toss with entire bottle of dressing.
Mix well.
Better served next day.

title: spinach dip
directions: Allow spinach to thaw. Chop scallions and water chestnuts into small pieces. Add all ingredients together (except spinach) and mix. After all is mixed well, add drained (make sure it's drained well) spinach and mix. Chill. Great with Sociables crackers and vegetable crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more or until center is set.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving 1/2 cup grated cheese for the top.
Place in casserole and bake for 45 minutes in a 450° oven. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix instant tea with remaining ingredients. Store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, add 2 parts water to 1 part mixture. Serve over ice.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine everything, except the soup, and form into balls. Place in deep casserole and cover with undiluted soup.
Bake, uncovered, for two hours at 325°.

title: grandma's dressing
directions: Mix corn meal, buttermilk and eggs for corn bread.
Bake at 350° until done.
Crumble biscuits in bowl and add milk.
Let stand.
Simmer until tender the celery, onion, margarine and 1 cup water.
Combine:
corn bread, biscuit mixture, onion-celery mix, chicken, chicken broth, chicken soup, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° until light brown on edges.

title: cheddar-broccoli noodles
directions: Cut chicken tenders into small pieces and fry until golden brown; set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Add noodles and broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until noodles and broccoli are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in seasoning packets; drain off most of liquid.
Add cheese soup, sour cream, pepper and chicken.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: one bowl dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add softened margarine; gradually add hot water to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour or enough flour to make thick batter.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: creamy broccoli cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in a bowl. Serve with vegetables, crackers.

title: cuban shredded beef
directions: Slice flank steak in strips (1/2-inch thick by 2 inches long). Use enough water to cover strips in pressure cooker.
Close lid; cook on high until steam comes out.
Put cap on lid; lower heat to medium.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add eggs and milk, stirring well. Add onion and blend (mixture will be thick).
Dip a large spoon into hot salad oil, then into batter for each hush puppy; drop by spoonfuls in hot salad oil.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cheese and potato wild rice soup
directions: Combine
wild
rice and water in saucepan and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Fry bacon pieces and onion
in
skillet until bacon is crisp.
Drain bacon and onion on paper towel.
Place soup in large saucepan; dilute as directed. Stir
in
milk
(1 quart), bacon, onion, cheese and cooked
rice. Stir
until
cheese
is
melted.
Garnish
with carrot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli spinach soup
directions: Heat water to boiling and add bouillon.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Transfer to blender or food processor and puree until smooth (in several portions, if necessary).
Reheat if necessary or serve at room temperature. Makes 6 servings at 40 calories each.

title: halloween party mix(16 cups)
directions: In large bowl, combine the pretzels, crackers and peanuts. In large pan, combine sugar, butter and corn syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and baking soda (mixture will foam). Pour over pretzel mixture and stir until coated. Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes. Break apart. Add M&M's and candy corn.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Set oven at 350°.
Put butter in casserole dish and put in oven to melt.
Make batter of 1 cup sugar, baking powder, flour and milk.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir.
Put sugared peaches on top; do not stir.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Can also use Monterey Jack, garlic Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese, too.
Best served in a little crock-pot to keep it warm and supply crackers to dip in.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Bake chicken in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to one hour until fully cooked.
In a medium saucepan, melt the margarine.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and baste the cooked chicken.
Cook the chicken for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: In a large pot, cover onions and potatoes with water.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
In large saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Add milk mixture and shrimp to the soup pot.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add half and half. Stir well and reheat.
Do not boil.
Add salt and pepper and serve. Yields 2 quarts.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: In a measuring cup, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Set aside.
Cream Crisco in large bowl.
Alternately add flour with 2 cups lukewarm water and salt.
When half the ingredients have been mixed, mix in yeast mix.
When all ingredients have been added, cover and refrigerated.
Make and let rise at least 2 hours before baking.

title: kentucky chocolate pie
directions: Blend together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: lemon fish
directions: Season fish with salt, pepper and garlic.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Cut up onion and green pepper.
Squeeze lemon juice over fish.
Put in covered dish.
Add onion, green pepper and s/c lemon over the entire dish.
Cook slow in oven for one hour.
Serve hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into the hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add soup, milk and chilies. Bring to a simmer.
The longer you cook, the hotter it will be.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet, over medium heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until done.
Set chicken aside.
In same pan, heat Prego sauce to a boil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Top chicken with cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti.
Top with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat, chopped onion and chopped bell pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce and let simmer for 10 minutes or until mixture is cooked good.
Cook rice in pan and rinse in a colander with cold water to keep rice from sticking together.
I leave both dishes in pans and we dip rice out and add as much meat mixture as we want on top of rice.
Very good.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Put soda in buttermilk. Sift dry ingredients together, adding alternately with the buttermilk.
Add eggs; blend and fold in jam and raisins.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 350° for about 1 or 1 1/2 hours according to your oven.
Test with toothpick.
I always line my pan with greased brown paper sack.

title: no stir peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour mixture into center of melted butter; do not stir.
Add peaches that have been sweetened with another cup of sugar.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Debone.
Combine sour cream and both soups and pour over chicken in dish.
Mix dressing mix with butter.
Pour broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients and place in dish.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool.
Poke holes all throughout cake.
Pour pineapple over top.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour over pineapple.
Arrange bananas over pudding.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans over top.

title: breadsticks(kid's corner)
directions: Brush the cut sides of buns with butter. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Combine cheese and seeds; sprinkle over buns. Bake at 450° for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish with wax paper; set aside.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, stirring gently.
Add butter; microwave, uncovered, at High for 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated through.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into prepared dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; mix thoroughly. Boil 1/2 minute. Mix in oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chocolate, nuts and coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: onion dip
directions: Bring water, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over onions and set overnight.
Drain well.
Add the 1/2 cup mayo and 1 teaspoon of celery seed.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Put sliced potatoes in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup with hamburger and oregano.
Pour over potatoes.
Pour Prego over hamburger.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over lasagna last 10 minutes of baking.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, onion and bacon.
Combine mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chicken with corn stuffing
directions: Combine soup, celery, onion and paprika.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Spread stuffing mix over, evenly.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard; spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pastry (8 or 9-inch)(double crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt with beater until soft peaks form. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add Karo, a little at a time, beating after each addition until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.

title: "philly" chocolate tunnel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, substituting margarine for oil.
Reserve 1 cup batter. Pour remaining batter into 12-cup greased and floured fluted tube pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in eggs, one at a time. Pour over batter in pan.
Spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Combine margarine, chocolate and corn syrup.
Pour over cooled cake. Makes 12 servings.
Preparation time: 15 minutes; cooking time: 35 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in large boiler, being careful not to get mixture on sides of pan.
Place over high heat. When mixture begins to steam, turn unit to low.
Cook mixture to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour one cup of cooked mixture over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining mixture to light to medium crack stage.
Gradually pour this mixture over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla. Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: galopita(greek baked custard)
directions: Heat milk. Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and farina.
Mix and cook until thick. Add butter and stir until melted.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add to mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon-sour cream coffee cake
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer, combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Blend in sour cream.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder into the creamed mixture; add vanilla.
Blend well.
Spoon half of batter into a 9-inch tube pan or a 10-inch Bundt pan which has been buttered and floured.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon-nut mixture over batter. Spoon in remaining batter and top with rest of nut mixture.
Place in cold oven, set at 350° and bake about 55 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Chop chestnuts and mix with beef and sausage; shape meat into balls and bake on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips in large pan; add peanuts and stir well.
Drop onto wax paper and refrigerate.

title: filling balls
directions: Form into balls and place in a well-greased dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: mom's beans
directions: Fry bacon and reserve grease.
In 9 x 11-inch pan, combine beans, onions, brown sugar and catsup.
Crumble bacon and add 2 tablespoons of the grease.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: skillet pork and sauerkraut
directions: Broil chops on preheated broiler 4 inches from heat 2 minutes on each side.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat until softened.
Add 1/4 cup water and remaining ingredients except apple.
Top with chops and simmer, covered, on low heat about 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Then stir in apple slices and simmer about 3 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: baked steamed rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender. Combine other ingredients and pour into casserole dish (13 x 9). Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garden turkey pockets
directions: Combine turkey (skinned and cooked without salt), carrots, celery and yogurt.
Stir well.
Cover and chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Chop beef.
Boil in water.
Add salt and pepper.
After beef is partially cooked, add vegetables and cook 15 minutes.
Add batter made of rest of ingredients.
Drop into stew.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients and chill about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and mash.
Add
sugar,
milk, eggs, margarine and coconut.
Place in casserole and bake 45 minutes or less at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole. Mix together all the other ingredients and pour over the chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly until it thickens. Cool. Fold apples and 1/2 cup of peanuts into mixture. Fold in Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining peanuts on top. Refrigerate overnight (but good same day too). Makes about 6 servings.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Put in casserole dish with parsley, chopped onion and cut butter all over.
Cook at 400° until potatoes are done.
While still hot, add bacon bits and grated cheese.
Pour Ranch dressing all over.
Cover all; let sit until all is melted.

title: basic loaf recipe
directions: Saute
vegetables
in
3 tablespoons water with garlic. Mix together
all
ingredients.
Loaf
should be moist but not runny. Bake in sprayed pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients gently, but well.
Put in low, flat casserole.
Toss corn flakes and nuts in margarine and put atop chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or if made ahead and refrigerated, increase baking time to 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, margarine, eggs and cheese together. Add and mix in vegetables.
Pour into a sprayed casserole dish. (Size 10 x 13-inch for thin casserole or 10 x 10-inch foil pan for thicker.)
Top with stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 bread pans, 9 x 5-inches.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Divide into two greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except hash browns and 1/2 of cheese.
Then mix in potatoes.
Pat in greased baking pan/dish.
Sprinkle on rest of the cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover while baking for 20 minutes and cook uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown beef with garlic, salt and chili powder; drain.
Mix soups and enchilada sauce.
Crush Doritos and put in bottom of dish.
Pour meat over Doritos.
Top with onions, chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese melts.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Add by teaspoons to taste to 1 cup hot water.

title: caramel popcorn(microwave)
directions: Put margarine, brown sugar, Karo syrup and butter flavoring in a microwave-safe dish and cook on High until it boils.
Stir and cook for 2 more minutes; then add baking soda and stir.
Put popcorn in a large brown grocery bag; pour syrup in and stir. Close top of bag and shake.
Microwave in bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and repeat 2 more times.
Pour into a large bowl and stir until dry.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add flour, soda and salt, sifted together.
Add vanilla, coconut, nutmeats and apples.
Pour into a large baking pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat off.
Add onion and potatoes; cook for about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, corn, salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes more.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef and drain. Add salt and pepper. Add mushroom soup and dry onion soup. Spread mixture evenly in the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Lay American cheese slices over the top. Cover the top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° until food thermometer reads 165°, about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cube squash and cook in salted water until crisp and tender. Drain.
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Stir in mushrooms and spaghetti mix.
Add squash, tomato paste and cheese.
Pour all ingredients into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Dice cooked chicken into large pieces.
Spread rice on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken and rice.
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Serves 12.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Spread cherries evenly over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour in pineapple, but do not mix.
Sift cake mix on top.
Pour butter on evenly.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and coconut is toasted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice.
Salt and pepper chicken and lay on top of rice.
Mix soups together and heat.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake in oven 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: frozen fudge fantasy(for all chocolate lovers!)
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until melted and smooth; take off of heat.
Add eggs.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Coat 9-inch spring-form pan with butter and cocoa powder.
Pour mixture in pan.
Place cookie sheet under the pan as it runs.
Bake 2 hours; turn oven off.
With door open, let sit in oven for 1/2 hour.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Remove from pan; put on plastic wrap in foil.
Freeze 6 to 12 hours and add whipped cream.

title: zesty stuffed vegetables
directions: Stir together cream cheese, pimento, olives, lemon juice and seasoning until well blended; set aside. Cut each pepper lengthwise into 6 wedges; remove seeds and membrane.

Cut cucumber into 12 slices, on the diagonal. Spoon the cheese mixture into a decorative bag or a heavy large food storage bag; snip one corner. Pipe the mixture onto the vegetables. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cake mix and eggs until well blended. Fold in pie filling. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin into large mixing bowl.
Break eggs into pumpkin and mix slowly in electric mixer.
Add sugar, coffee cream, milk, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into crusts.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour, then lower temperature to 350° to 375° and bake another 1/2 hour or until testing knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken breasts.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Grease the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place cooked chicken in dish and top with soup mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/2 bag of chips with all other ingredients, except cheese.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with cheese and remaining chips.
Bake until cheese melts and casserole is warm, about 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel sticks, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool 1 hour or more.

title: rice casserole
directions: In butter, saute
onions until pale yellow.
Place in large casserole. Add remaining ingredients, let stand all day.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Into medium size bowl sift flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar.
With pastry blender cut in shortening until quite fine pieces.
Add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough follows fork around the bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board and gently knead a few times just to smooth out dough.
Pat or roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Gather scraps of dough.
Gently mix together and press out.
Cut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Gives baking powder a chance to start action and they bake up lighter. Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients on High 4 minutes. Stir. Microwave 4 more minutes on High. Stir. Add butter and vanilla. Stir and microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Add soda and stir and pour on greased baking sheet.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream Wesson oil, sugar and applesauce.
Add baking powder, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and salt; stir to blend.
Mix together flour, raisins and nuts; add to batter.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Chop chicken in blender.
Place in bottom of baking dish. Mix dressing according to directions on box and spread on top of chicken.
Heat soup and milk in saucepan until blended.
Pour over dressing.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until heated, approximately 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put Rice Chex in a bowl.
In a separate pan, mix chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine and melt.
Dump over Rice Chex. In a grocery bag, put powdered sugar.
Dump in mix.
Shake well (until all are white).

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it strings (dip spoon in mixture, let drip, cook until it make a thread-like string).
Add peanuts and boil until peanuts turn in color (295° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add soda, mixing well and quickly.
Mixture will be foamy.
Immediately spread as thin as possible onto large buttered cookie sheet or greased marble slab. After cooled, break up into pieces.
Store in covered container. Makes 36 servings.

title: regal chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, drained pineapple, grapes, celery and peanuts.
Stir in tarragon.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Gently fold into chicken mixture. Serve on lettuce with parsley or small celery leaves as a garnish. Serves 8.

title: lady ashburnham pickles
directions: Cut very fine as for relish the cukes, peeled and with seeds removed.
Add 1/4 cup of salt and let stand overnight.
Drain in morning and add onions, chopped fine, vinegar, sugar, flour, turmeric, dry mustard, mustard and celery seed.
Cook 1 hour and put in hot jars.

title: perfect iced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done.
Mash potato (do not add anything). Then add powdered sugar to dough consistency.
Roll out to about 1/16-inch thick.
Spread peanut butter all over.
Roll up and slice.
May add food coloring at beginning for color.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam. Divide mixture between pans.
Top with catsup or barbecue sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in hot water. Add juice from pineapple. Chill until set.
Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese. Add pineapple. Beat well with gelatin mixture. Add pecans and whipped cream.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cut cantaloupe into about 1-inch cubes.
Place in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and salt and sprinkle over cantaloupe.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with margarine. Bake at 425° until thick and brown.

title: sunday potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
I haven't found anyone who didn't love this dish.
Freezes well also.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until done. Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs in bowl. Stuff shells with mixture. Line in a 9 x 12- inch baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over stuffed shells and top with cheese. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes. Let sit for 15 minutes, then serve.

title: filled mocha thumbprints
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup frosting.
In large bowl, combine remaining frosting, graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Blend well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and immediately roll each ball in ground nuts.
With finger, make imprint in center of each ball. Place in single layer in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake 30 or 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, salt, lemon juice, onion juice and pimentos.
Add chicken, celery and hard-boiled eggs; stir gently to coat.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and then top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
Excellent when served with spiced peaches and soft rolls.
Spice peaches with sprinkles of one or more of your favorite spices, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cloves, etc.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Pat in 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Blend 4 eggs, 2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Add 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder; pour over crust and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fantastic cheesecake
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Add cream cheese and mix until blended and creamy. Blend in sugar, then eggs. Add cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.

title: no-name cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix (bake in oblong pan).
Let cake cool on serving platter.
Beat softened cream cheese.
Add milk, then package of instant pudding; mix well.
Spread on top (not sides) of cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over that (not sides). Spread Cool Whip over entire cake.
Then place strawberries on Cool Whip after you have washed them.
Keep refrigerated.

title: never fail potato salad
directions: Cook cubed potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain well.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, celery seed, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Add onion, celery and sweet pickles.
Add mayonnaise mixture to potatoes.
Toss lightly to coat mixture.
Carefully fold in chopped eggs.
Cover tightly and chill.
Makes about eight servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: *Three level tablespoons of cocoa + 1 tablespoon of oil = 1 square chocolate.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Add melted butter and vanilla.

title: best fudge
directions: In a 6 to 8 quart container heat together candy bars, broken into pieces, marshmallow cream, butter, vanilla and semi-sweet morsels.
In a 4 to 6 quart sauce pan combined granulated sugar and evaporated milk.
Let sugar and milk come to a hard boil. Cook stirring constantly for 6 minutes.
Pour sugar and evaporated milk over remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth and creamy. Fold in chopped pecans. Pour mixture into a cook tray or jelly roll pan lined with wax paper.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours until completely set before removing. Yield:
6 pounds fudge.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Vegetables:
Green onions, chopped broccoli, cauliflower, shredded carrots, green peppers and whatever you have.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and add Eagle Brand milk.
Blend in lemon juice and vanilla.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with cherry pie filling and put 1 fresh cherry in center.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator before baking.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 16 to 19 minutes.
Batter can be frozen or kept tightly covered in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: orange-buttermilk shake
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender; mix on high speed until smooth (or beat all ingredients with rotary beater).
Yields 2 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: herb baked chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Wash chicken; put in colander to drain and wipe dry with paper towel.
Prepare chicken first and set aside.
Place chicken in large baking plan flat and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours. Cover with wax paper.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, soak bread crumbs in cream.
Mix in meat thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except shortening. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown and cook meatballs.
Serve meatballs from chafing dish.
Keep "seconds" warm in the oven.
Makes 25 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and seed peppers and grind together with the onions. Scald and let set for 5 minutes, then scald for the second time and drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt and cook for about 15 minutes to thicken.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix together.
Drop into greased muffin tins.
Yields 12 rolls.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 250° in a tube pan.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut the salt pork into 1-inch pieces and simmer for one hour. Wash and remove the wilted leaves of the cabbage, cut into the size you want.
Add the cabbage, carrots and potatoes to the salt pork. Simmer until vegetables are cooked.
With this recipe, you can also cook it in 1 pint of milk and 1/4 cup flour to give it creamy sauce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs; add buttermilk and vanilla. Melt margarine separately and add dry ingredients. Add egg mixture and pour into small pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into freezer can of a 5-quart hand turn or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour before eating.

title: scripture bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In another large bowl, sift together next 3 ingredients.
Chop next 2 ingredients; add with last ingredient to sifted mixture.
If entirely too thick to spread, add a little bit more of second ingredient.
Spread in buttered and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack before cutting into small bars.
Makes about 50.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small, bite size pieces. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough brown gravy to cover. Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added.
But do this only in an emergency as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: tarragon chicken and rice(serves 4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook for 6 minutes, turning once, or until lightly browned but not cooked through.
With slotted spoon, remove to a plate.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325 ° for 2 hours. Onion and/or bacon may be added for flavor, and I think they greatly improve the beans.

title: salmon loaf supreme
directions: About 1 hour before serving, start heating oven to 375°.
In large bowl with fork, combine bread crumbs, milk, eggs, salt, Tabasco, m.s.g. and poultry seasoning until mixed.
Add chunks of salmon with fork; mix well.
Lightly turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; smooth off top.
Bake for 45 minutes or until firm in center.
Turn out.
Place right side up on heated platter. Serve, sliced, with peaches as the garnish and Creamy Pea and Scallion Sauce over each slice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baby food bundt cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add all ingredients together (except flour), then add flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(I bake at 325° after about 15 or 20 minutes.)

title: white chocolate crispy treats
directions: Melt white chocolate in double boiler over medium heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir as needed.
Remove from heat.
Combine nuts and crisp cereal in a bowl.
Pour melted chocolate and peanut butter over mixture; stir in marshmallows.
Use a teaspoonful to drop small amount of mixture onto wax paper; let cool.

title: tuna fish and egg bows salad(italian)
directions: Cook bows according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Chop vegetables and mix well with bows, salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine pickles and mayonnaise.
Add vegetable mixture. Arrange tuna fish on top. Serve on bed of lettuce. Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation time:
15 to 20 minutes. Cooking time:
10 to 12 minutes.

title: glazed chicken breasts
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly combine onion soup mix, preserves and water; set aside.
In an aluminum foil-lined broiler pan, arrange chicken breasts and peppers.
Top with soup mixture. Broil 20 minutes or until chicken is done, turning once while broiling.
Serve over hot rice.

title: scotch treasure bar cookies
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar.
Add quick oats, baking powder and salt.
Press into greased or buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lacy's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Form a loaf and place in loaf pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk in buttered 1 1/2-quart dish and arrange layer of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake in 375° oven 1 hour and uncover and bake 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry ground meat and onions. When done, drain off fat and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or a large casserole dish. Cook potatoes and drain, leaving 1/2 cup of water in potatoes. Put butter in potatoes. Add mixed vegetables and mix well. Pour over ground meat mixture. Pour creamed corn over entire mixture. Mix Jiffy cornbread as directed on box. Pour over all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese crisps(appetizer)
directions: Combine butter, cheese, flour, hot sauce and salt.
Mix well. Gently fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape into walnut size balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine and put in greased casserole dish.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups.
Pour milk over cereal in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until brown and firm at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian chili
directions: Fry the burger, sausage, onion and green pepper in the butter.
When cooked, add cumin, hot sauce, Tabasco and salsa. Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add V-8 juice.
Bring to boil and add pasta.
Cook until pasta is just tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: italian spaghetti frittata
directions: Julienne the green pepper and zucchini.
Slice onion thin. Finely chop the garlic.
Peel the tomatoes; seed and drain.
Beat eggs and Parmesan together.
In a 12-inch nonstick omelet pan, saute green pepper and onion until onion begins to brown.
Add tomatoes and garlic; saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, zucchini and drained spaghetti.
Toss until well mixed.
Pour egg and Parmesan mixture over the contents in pan.
Cook until eggs begin to set and mixture browns.
Slide Frittata onto an oiled plate. Invert pan over the Frittata; flip over and fry on the other side until brown.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, oil and eggs together.
Blend in vanilla and sour milk.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt together and add to batter, mixing well.
Blend in zucchini. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and serve cold.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 45 minutes with plenty of water. Remove chicken and add bouillon cubes; stir in cream of chicken soup.
Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add milk; mix and put on floured board.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness, then cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop into pot of boiling broth and cook about 15 minutes.
Cover pan and reduce heat for cooking time.
Cut up chicken and add to dumplings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, continually beating. Add dry ingredients to oil.
Mix thoroughly. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
To bake, form small balls and place on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Press with glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°, 12 to 13 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix all together (soften ice cream).
Pour into pan and freeze.
Can serve with chocolate sauce.
Great for children's party.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Combine graham crackers and 1/4 cup sugar; add gradually to softened butter; stir in water.
Press into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup of the milk for 5 minutes.
Scald rest of milk.
Separate eggs; beat yolks slightly; add 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Pour scalded milk over them gradually while stirring.
Return to heat and cook, stirring until custard coats spoon.
Remove from heat and add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold into custard; add brandy and nutmeg.
Chill until thickened.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set and top with whipped cream.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
To serve, add 3 tablespoons of mix in a cup of boiling water.

title: microwave autumn soup
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and celery in 5-quart casserole. Microwave on High (100%) until ground beef loses its pink color, 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all other ingredients in 5-quart saucepan.
Add ground beef and cook until cabbage is tender, then drain.
Take 1/4 cup of mix and place in corner of one egg roll wrapper.
Roll wrapper to corner.
Fold over opposite ends. Continue rolling.
Dab water on edges to seal.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: chickpeas with tahini (ground sesame seed)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix until chickpeas are smooth.
Store hummus in covered container in refrigerator. Serve well chilled.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
More garlic may be added, if desired.
Thin with additional lemon juice if served as dip with chips.

title: super easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased muffin pan about 2/3 full at 425° until lightly brown. The dough can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; mix with graham crackers.
Spread and pack in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat 2 eggs, 2 sticks margarine (soft) and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust and slice bananas until covered.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle nuts.
Place a cherry on each serving or cutting size; drizzle with syrup over top.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: silver cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl. Add Crisco and first cup milk called for in the recipe. Beat vigorously by hand or electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add egg whites, additional 1/3 cup milk and lemon flavoring. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into two 9-inch layer pans which have been greased with Crisco and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange rice and chicken
directions: To start, take whole chicken and boil in about 8 to 10 cups of water and chicken bouillon cubes; makes broth. Have this ready to go before beginning rest of recipe.

title: smothered okra
directions: Simmer onion and pepper in oil for approximately 5 minutes. Add okra, then tomato sauce.
Let simmer; cover for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls(makes approximately 50)
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands until well blended.
Shape into small balls and bake on cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm.
Freezes well.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese together. Add pimentos, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, cayenne and salt.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into a ball and roll into finely chopped pecans.

title: butter gooey cake
directions: Mix with electric mixer until creamy.
Pour on top of cake. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with xxx when cool.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and warm on Medium power in microwave until cheese melts (not too hot; do it slowly).
Serve with rye crackers or pumpernickel bread.

title: caramel chews candy
directions: Melt caramels and cream in double boiler or microwave. Gradually add other ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Makes two dozen.

title: taco pie(sandy kartheiser)
directions: Separate rolls; pat them around pie tin.
Press chips into dough.
Brown meat.
Drain grease.
Add seasoning plus water. Bring to boil and simmer.
Blend in sour cream and add to pie crust.
Sprinkle grated cheese and more corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In large mixing bowl, mash hot potatoes.
When all lumps are removed, add cream cheese in small pieces and then butter.
Beat well until cheese and butter are both melted and well mixed.
Mix in sour cream.
To the milk, add eggs and onions.
Add to the potato mixture along with the salt and pepper.
Beat well until fluffy.
Place in a greased casserole dish and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Combine spread and yogurt.
Add dry ingredients and strawberry mixture to creamed mixture (beginning and ending with dry ingredients).
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mini hamburger loaves
directions: Combine ingredients and form into mini loaves.
Put loaves in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sauce.
Bake.

title: magical mayo cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend all dry ingredients; set aside.
In a small bowl, blend all wet ingredients and add to dry ingredients, mixing well.

title: aunt pat's frozen dessert
directions: Mix peanut butter and maple syrup.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put half mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream on top of mixture.
Put rest of Krispies mixture on top.
Freeze.
Enjoy!

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Stir in chicken.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Drain pineapple (leave some juice); pour over butter and brown sugar.
Mix cake as directed.
Pour over pineapple mix.
Bake until cake is done (350°) for about 1 hour.
When done, turn upside down.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and pat in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Rinse.
Combine ham and 3/4 cup cheese. Combine soup, milk and onion.
Place 1/2 noodles in bottom of 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 ham and cheese mixture over noodles. Pour 1/2 soup mixture over ham mixture.
Repeat 1, 2, 3.
Sprinkle top with rest of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain
juice
off
of canned corn, beans and peas.
Mix all ingredients together, then put into refrigerator.
Let set 24 hours before serving.

title: casserole of shrimp
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine butter and mushrooms 2 to 3 minutes on High in microwave, stirring once.
Stir in soup, soy sauce and white pepper.
Microwave on High 3 minutes or until hot. Stir once.
Stir in shrimp and sour cream.
Cover with lid and cook on Medium in microwave 4 to 5 minutes or until heated.
Stir once.
Serve over rice.

title: oriental marinade for beef or chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Pour over chicken or steak.
Marinate 4 to 6 hours.
Turn once during marinating.
Grill!

title: sunday chicken  soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in 1/4 cup butter.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes.
Heat milk and
broth to boiling.
Slowly add vegetables.
Stir constantly.
Add rice, pimento, chicken and parsley.
Simmer until thick.

title: 1st prize rice
directions: Make white sauce in given proportions of milk, flour and margarine.
Add cheese, olives, seasoning and grated onion.
When cheese is melted, pour over rice in casserole and bake half hour at 375°.

title: red snapper
directions: Combine onion, orange juice, oil, orange peel and salt in greased (12 x 8 x 2-inch) pan.
Arrange snapper fillets in this mixture, turning to coat evenly.
Leave at room temperature for 30 minutes (lightly cover dish).
Add nutmeg and pepper.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until fillets flake easily.
Baste. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl with mixer on high.
Mix for 4 to 5 minutes or until smooth.
Line muffin pan with bake cups.
Pour batter in bake cups (2-inches).
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer until mixture thickens.
Serve on any meat of your choice.
Store unused portion in the refrigerator.

title: eggplant bake
directions: Sprinkle eggplant in colander with 1 1/4 teaspoons salt.
Let drain 30 minutes.
Place tomatoes, cut side down, on paper towels. Drain 30 minutes.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Saute garlic and onion.
Discard garlic; don't break onion into rings.
Drain. Rinse eggplant and drain.
Brush with oil and broil 5 minutes; turn and repeat.
Arrange in alternating layers, slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle with spices and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together	butter,
sugar	and vanilla; add potato chips and pecans.
Stir
in
flour.
Form
mixture
into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and press thin with a glass that has been dipped in sugar and a little flour.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes until light brown (golden).

title: pastry for 9-inch pie
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl. Cut in shortening using a pastry blender or fork until the pieces are the size of small peas. (For extra tender pastry, cut half the shortening into the flour and salt until the mixture looks like cornmeal. Then cut in remaining shortening until the mixture looks like small peas.) Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of

mixture. Gently toss with fork; push to side of bowl. Sprinkle next tablespoon of water over dry part; mix lightly. Push to moistened part at side. Repeat until all is moistened. Form into ball. Flatten ball on lightly floured surface. Roll from center to edge until dough is 1/8-inch thick. Fit pastry into 9-inch pie plate. Trim 1/2 to 1-inch beyond edge; fold under and flute. Prick bottom and sides well with a fork. Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: heritage coleslaw(serves 8)
directions: Place all the ingredients into a suitable container, toss and refrigerate.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in clean jar.
To make hot tea, add 1 teaspoon to 1 tablespoon mix to a cup of hot water.
May be made in microwave very easy.
You may reduce sugar and add a small amount of Equal or Sweet 'N Low.

title: feta veggie pasta
directions: Soak sun dried tomatoes in warm water for 30 minutes.
Cook rotini as directed (al dente).
Cook chopped broccoli in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add red pepper and chopped sun dried tomatoes to broccoli.
Cook 1 minute in microwave.
Saute chopped garlic in oil until hot.
Add vegetables, chopped Feta cheese and garlic and oil to rotini.
Cover with parsley and serve.

title: fantastic apple bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each. Stir in milk and apples.
Mix dry ingredients and stir in.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn out and cool on rack.

title: chess pie
directions: Put butter, sugar and vinegar in a bowl and melt thoroughly. Then add to 3 slightly beaten eggs.
Stir well, but do not use electric mixer.
Add vanilla and pour into an unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then at 300° until set.
Do not overcook.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Put cabbage on top of meat mixture.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes. Cook until cabbage is done, then serve.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Then add the rest of the ground up ingredients. Put in refrigerator to set.
Excellent for Thanksgiving.

title: mushrooms-spinach casserole
directions: Wash spinach; cook in small amount of water 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well.
Wash and pat dry mushrooms.
Slice and saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat sauce, stirring until smooth and cheese is melted.
Layer spinach, mushrooms and sauce in greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening,
sugar,
brown sugar, vanilla, peanut butter,
eggs
and	water.	Beat
creamed
ingredients
for
2 minutes.
Mix flour, soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Add to creamed mixture and beat
1 minute more.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 11 minutes at 325°.

title: hot panini sandwiches
directions: In food processor, mix 1 part sun dried tomatoes and 1/4 part water until pasty.
Cut Foccaio bread into 4 x 4-inch squares and slice so that you have two 4 x 4-inch sides of bread.
Lightly brush bread with olive oil.
Spread tomato mixture on the bottom side of bread.
Place 2 ounces of chicken breast on top of tomato mixture.
Put 2 leaves of fresh basil on chicken, broken into small pieces.
Put 1 ounce of cheese on top of basil and chicken.
Cover with top slice of bread.
Grill or bake until cheese is melted.

title: real cajun roux
directions: Note:
Always use equal amounts of flour and cooking oil for whatever quantity of roux you desire.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef if not already cooked. Add frozen vegetables and bring to a boil. Lower heat; add remaining ingredients (except tomatoes). Keep a check on the water content and add more as needed. Cook until potatoes and vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes; cook another 15 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: ambrosia bavarian salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water. Stir in orange juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy and light. Stir in whipped topping until well blended. Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut.
Pour into a large serving bowl. Chill until firm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 1 cup sugar and press in 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Take Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; mix and spread on pretzels.
Put pineapple and cornstarch in saucepan; bring to a boil until thickens.
Spread on top of cream mixture.
Chill!

title: stephen king's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast.
Add milk, sugar, salt, shortening and half the flour; mix until smooth.
Mix in rest of flour until dough
is easy to handle.
Knead on floured surface until smooth (10 minutes should do it).
Put in greased bowl, cover with dish towel and let it rise about an hour, until double.
Divide dough in half, shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Brush with butter and let rise another hour.
Bake at 425° about 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.
To test for doneness, tap to see if they sound hollow. Brush with butter, if you like.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: baked ham
directions: The sausage patties should be no more than 1/2 inch thick. They should be cooked slowly so as not to destroy the taste of the spices.
