Turn often so the sausage will cook all the way through.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine squash, onion and pepper with salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed; bring to boil.
Add squash, onion and green pepper; boil 3 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Blend oil and brown sugar.
Stir in egg.
Blend flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cook 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Serve Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese with strawberries, sliced apples and orange slices.

title: lentil soup ii
directions: In soup pot, combine lentils, beef stock, onion, carrots, celery, cloves, pepper, parsley, thyme and ham hock.
Bring to boil; turn down to simmer.
Cook, covered, 35 minutes, or until lentils are tender.
Remove ham hock and set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer 1 can refried beans mixed with salsa or taco sauce and sour cream mixed with taco seasoning.
Top with onion, pepper, cheese, tomatoes, black olives or whatever you choose.
Dip in unseasoned taco chips.

title: chess pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 400°, then bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Place rice, vegetables, 1/2 cup French fried onions around and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half.
Take out yolks.
Mash fine; add all ingredients but paprika.
Mix until smooth.
(May need a little more liquid, if so use pickle juice or salad dressing.)
Place mixture back in egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.
Can decorate with olives.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Prepare noodles as per package directions. Add all soups but only 1/2 the water required for soups.
Heat over low heat until bubbling.

title: mexicorn dip
directions: Drain corn and place in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with tostitos.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and enough powdered sugar to make a pie dough consistency.
Roll between wax paper.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Slice.

title: rum butter sweets
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Cream margarine; add sugar, salt and flavoring and cream well.
Add flour gradually.
Shape into balls the size of a marble.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a hole in the center of each ball.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until delicately browned.
Fill with Creamy Pecan Filling while warm. Cool before frosting.

title: blue ribbon winner wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Add strawberry gel and cut up strawberries together.
Put in cooled pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put strawberries on top to make it look nice.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in a casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix remainder of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole with melted oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven until sides are brown.

title: kids party punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid with water and sugar; mix well.
Add 7-Up and stir.
Garnish with thin slices of orange and/or lemon.
Slice thinly so they will float in punch bowl.

title: main dish casserole
directions: Brown turkey in a little oil.
Add 2 cups water and mixed vegies.
Throw in the noodles and stir.
Cover pot and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add the soup mix and more water if it needs it. Let simmer until all the vegies are done.
Don't let it suck up all the liquid.
Real good with corn bread.
Serves 4.

title: philadelphia butter cake
directions: In a bowl, put the cake mix.
Melt the butter and pour into cake mix.
With a fork, mix until it forms a dough.
Press mixture into glass baking dish.
Mix softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour over the cake mixture. Bake 25 to 28 minutes at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Do not let bottom overcook. Cool and enjoy.

title: crab and cheese appetizer
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise and pepper; stir in cheese and onions. Gently stir in crab. Bake at 325° until puffed and golden. Serve warm with crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix browned meat and onion with other ingredients.
Top with the remaining Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding over top of fruit, except bananas.
Do not stir in pudding.
Let set in fridge for 24 hours.
Then cut up bananas. Mix well and serve.

title: pineapple party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, cranberry juice, lemonade concentrate, sugar and food coloring, if used. Just before serving, pour in the ginger ale.
Garnish with ice ring or serve over ice.
Makes 36 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: easy cheese bread 2
directions: Combine biscuit mix and cheese in a large bowl. Combine egg and milk. Add to biscuit mix, stirring vigorously for 2 minutes. Spoon into a lightly greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chinese style country ribs
directions: Combine soy sauce, marmalade, catsup and garlic. Brush on both sides of ribs. Place in slow cooker. Pour remaining sauce over all. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken, broccoli and ziti
directions: In
a large frypan fry and simmer the chicken in 2 tablespoons of butter.
When the chicken is 80% cooked remove it from the pan and place it in a large bowl and set aside.
In another large pan saute the garlic and onions in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Once sauteed, add the chicken broth with 1/2 cup of water, then add the chicken bouillon, parsley and pepper.
Simmer until the seasoning has dissolved, then add the Velveeta and American cheese.
Stir occasionally, until the cheese has melted, then add the cooked chicken.
Simmer and stir occasionally.
Cook the broccoli (do not overcook).
Add sour cream to the sauce mixture that is simmering. Keep the sauce stirred, you don't want to burn it.
Cook the ziti in lightly salted water (don't overcook).
Drain the ziti, however, do not rinse.
Put ziti back into pot.
Pour the sauce mixture into the ziti pot and mix.
Pour all into a baking pan; sprinkle top with grated cheese, if desired, and place the cooked broccoli on top.
Bake in preheated oven a 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: chicken-sour cream casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; cool.
Remove chicken from bone.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs, mixing well.
Spoon 1/2 of crumbs into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper. Pour over chicken and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in melted butter. Add shrimp and ham.
Fry about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Add seasoning and liquid.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer until rice is done, about 30 minutes. Serves 4.
Use soy sauce if you like.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add salt and baking soda and sift again.
Put aside.
Cream butter well; add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately, beating until well mixed.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased tube pan.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Scramble eggs until firm; break up into small pieces. Set aside.
Marinate chicken pieces with 1/2 soy sauce, cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Heat oil in frying pan (medium-high heat).
Fry chicken pieces, separating pieces at the same time, for 2 1/2 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Set aside.
Using the same frying pan, stir-fry onion, green onion and frozen peas for 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add cooked rice, soy sauce and oyster sauce.
Mix and stir; add cooked egg and chicken.
Mix well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix by hand.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients, except eggs. Beat egg slightly and add to mixture.
Add melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set in center.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef, sausage, regular rice, onion, garlic, 1 can tomato sauce and seasonings in bowl.
Prepare cabbage by simmering in boiling water until tender.
Remove core before placing in water.
Roll meat mixture into sausage link shape and wrap with cabbage leaves.
Place seam side down in heavy baking pan. Cover with sauerkraut and juice and second can of tomato sauce.
Add enough water to partially cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Cover loosely with foil for first 2 hours.
Makes 20 to 24 rolls. Reheats well.

title: dorothy's old fashioned saltwater dills
directions: Bring to boil. Place cucumbers in sterilized jars, wide-mouth if possible. In each jar, place a clove of fresh garlic, hot pepper, if desired, a fresh grape leaf and fresh green dill. Pour the boiling brine over the cucumbers. Seal tightly and store about 30 days.

title: easy brown hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, dash of salt, sugar and baking powder; beat.
Add butter and eggs.
Add enough flour so dough will be easy to handle and thoroughly knead the dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl and allow dough to rise. Punch it down and it is ready to cook.
You may spoon batter into greased muffin pans or cut rolls out.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: finger steaks
directions: Trim round steaks and slice in desired size.
Dip into egg and milk mixture, then roll in Frosted Flakes and flour (mixed together, just enough flour to make Frosted Flakes stick).
Fry in butter (using margarine or oil gives a different taste).

title: lemon delight
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and nuts; press into bottom of dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh salsa picante
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: batter rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl (use mixer).
Beat in egg.
Mix yeast and 2 cups flour separately.
Add separate mix to liquid and beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour (or enough for a very soft dough).
Cover bowl with towel and let rise for about 30 minutes or until doubled.
Punch down and place in well-greased muffin pan.
Let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: country dinner hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger with several strips of bacon, cut up.
In separate bowl, cut up onion.
Add beans and remaining ingredients. Add hamburger and bacon; stir well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine the flour, salt and sugar in a medium bowl.
Beat the eggs and add the buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans in an oiled 7-cup ring mold and press cheese mixture into mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on platter and pat remaining pecans onto cheese ring.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve on crackers with strawberry preserves.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: You can prepare this early in the day or even weeks ahead and freeze it.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken overnight.
Brush with olive oil before grilling.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix one stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat out into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine; beat until thick.
If needed, add another cup of sugar.
Spread over top of crumb mixture.
Slice bananas on top of mixture. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Mix nuts with Cool Whip; spread over pineapple.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a spread.
Cut Pepperidge Farm French loaves into thin slices and spread mixture evenly on bread. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen. Increase baking time 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hungarian cheese dumplings
directions: Place cheese in bowl.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add salt and flour and mix.
On floured board, knead lightly until smooth and it doesn't stick to hands.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling, salted water.
Cook until dumplings rise to the top or until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Fry onion in butter; pour over dumplings.
Serve with sour cream.

title: silver diet dinner for two
directions: Place 1 chicken piece and half of the remaining ingredients on each of 2 foil squares.
Seal tightly.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: elderberry crisp
directions: Place the elderberries in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together the next 7 ingredients.
Crumble over berries.
Pour the melted oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown on top.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and place in a large, greased casserole dish or 2 smaller ones.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: french custard toast
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a shallow pan and add a dash of salt. Cut bread diagonally about 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick.
Place bread in egg mixture and soak for 15 minutes on each side.
Heat oleo in a large skillet and fry bread slowly (about 5 minutes each side) until brown.
Serve hot.
You may use syrup, honey or jam over bread, or sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: applesauce cake (chocolate)
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven 1 hour.

title: fruit delight
directions: Place fruit in large bowl.
Combine vanilla mix, Tang and pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and stir gently.
Chill before serving.

title: banana boat
directions: Keeping the banana in its skin, make 2 cuts, forming a "V" opening along the length of the banana.
Put it aside.
It will be used later.

title: rise and shine
directions: Cook sausage until done (well browned).
Slice bread about 1/2-inch thick and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain sausage and spoon over bread (reserve 1/2 cup).
Now beat eggs and milk together; pour this over the sausage and bread.
Top with remaining sausage and cheese.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in pecans (crushed).
Add Tabasco sauce, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of Tater Tots in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Brown hamburger meat.
Add onion and cook until done; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese.
Pour over Tater Tots and place remaining Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and browned on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, milk, 2 egg yolks and 1 whole egg (save other egg whites for meringue).
Cook until thick on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.
Cool.
Serve.

title: oven barbecued meat balls
directions: In a bowl, moisten the bread crumbs with the milk and combine them with the meat, salt and pepper.
Shape the mixture into 24 meat balls and place them in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients to make the barbecue sauce.
Pour the sauce over the meat balls and bake them, covered, at 475° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave texas meatballs and rice
directions: Mix ground
beef,
egg,
chili powder, salt and pepper. Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Place in 2 quart casserole. Microwave on High
until
meatballs
are set and lose the pink color (4 to 7
minutes), rearranging meatballs after half the cooking time. Drain.
Stir
in remaining ingredients.
Cover. Microwave on High until
mixture
is	bubbly	and
onions are tender (4 to
7 minutes).
Stir
after half the cooking time. Let stand until rice is tender (2 to 3 minutes).

title: seven layer torte cake
directions: Make instant pudding as directed per package.
Mix the flour, butter, sugar and nuts together.
Press the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch flat pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring 8
cups water to a boil.	Add tea bags and remove from heat. Keep covered for 5 minutes. Add sugar.
Boil 4 cups water. Add cloves and simmer for 5 minutes. Mix tea and clove water
with orange
juice,
lemon
juice and pineapple juice. Makes about 1 gallon. Serve warm.

title: raisin-cinnamon batter loaf
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups of the flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and undissolved yeast in large bowl.
Combine milk, water and butter in saucepan.
Heat to very warm (120° to 130°).
Gradually add to flour-yeast mixture.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup of the flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in raisins and enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 50 minutes.
Stir down.
Turn into 2 well-greased 1 1/2-quart casseroles.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 40 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from casseroles; cool on racks.
Makes 2.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saut bell pepper and onion in bacon drippings until onions are translucent.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir gently. Cover and simmer until okra is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole supreme
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Mix together soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, carrots and onions.
Mix broccoli in the sauce.
Melt butter.
Mix in bread crumbs and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in frozen orange juice.
Add pineapple (with juice).
Drain oranges; add.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dried tomato focaccia
directions: * Chives (1/4 cup), oregano (3/4 teaspoon) and rosemary (1/2 teaspoon may be substituted for dried herbs.
Also, as a variation, substitute 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour.

title: rich party nut rolls
directions: Soften yeast a little in milk.
Add remaining milk and beaten egg yolks.
Mix shortening into flour and salt.
Add liquid to make a soft dough.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out as pie crust on sugar sprinkled lightly floured board and cut into pieces about 3 x 4-inches.
Make a paste of the walnuts, egg whites, sugar and salt. Spread onto the dough and make into tiny rolls.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: oreo cookie dessert(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook pudding as directed and cool.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole Oreos.
Spread cooled pudding on top.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Oreos.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Combine and press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: golden baked potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and cut in small chunks.
Moisten with water. Mix cheese, salt, pepper and flour in a paper sack.
Drop potatoes into sack and shake to coat.
Pout coated potatoes in shallow baking pan.
Melt butter and drizzle over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 375°, turning once after 30 minutes.

title: orange peel cup
directions: Cut one
orange in half, remove and eat the pulp.
Fill the cavity
with an egg or hamburger.
Place on a bed of coals and cook until done.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 10-inch baking dish in oven. Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder. Stir in milk and mix until blended. Spoon batter over melted margarine. Heat berries with 2 tablespoons sugar just until hot. Pour over batter in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden. Serve warm.

title: turkey medallions with orange teriyaki sauce(light and easy)
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat in 2 teaspoons corn oil, cook celery, onion, salt and ginger until tender.
In medium bowl, mix turkey, vegetable mix, horseradish and 1 tablespoon chopped parsley until blended.
With slightly dampened hands, shape turkey mixture into 8 medallions.

title: friendship
directions: Lay chicken on its back on a flat work surface.
Using a sharp knife, make a cut between the leg.
Bend the leg away from the body and press fingertips into the back of the joint to pop the joint loose.
Continue to cut leg away from breast, then make a cut through the joint connecting the drumstick and the thigh.
A thin line of fat over the joint will act as a cutting guide.

title: spinach balls
directions: Salt, pepper, garlic powder and thyme to taste.
Cook spinach and drain very well.
Combine all ingredients and roll into balls, using about 1 teaspoon mixture for each.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Remove from cookie sheet at once and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 75 balls.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Slice bananas and spread over crust.
Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and sugar; spread over bananas.
Spread crushed pineapple over condensed milk mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and cherries on top. Refrigerate to set.
Serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados to a lumpy consistency.
Mix all ingredients except the garlic.
Stick the toothpicks with garlic into the mixture.
Refrigerate.
Remove toothpicks with garlic before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend egg yolks and milk.
Stir in the pancake mix.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Fold in the corn. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into mixture.
Pour cooking oil into an iron skillet a half to 1-inch deep and heat. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: molasses coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and oleo into very fine crumbs.
Set 1 1/2 cups aside to use as topping.
In large bowl, combine Brer Rabbit, boiling water and baking soda; add the crumbs and mix by hand very well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey-wild rice casserole
directions: Use half of seasoning mix in rice mix.
Combine all ingredients and let stand overnight in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, salt and pepper together.
Shape into meatballs.
Combine Rice-A-Roni seasoning packet with 2 1/2 cups of water; pour over meat.
Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: classic baked mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as directed.
Combine pasta, meat, spaghetti sauce and 2 c. of cheese in large bowl and mix well.
Turn into greased 9x13 pan.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover and top with remaining cheese. Bake additional 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: angel hair primavera
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Place pasta in large serving bowl.

title: jello pies
directions: Place can of milk in freezer until cold.
Combine eggs, sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook over medium to low heat until eggs are cooked, approximately 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello to mixture while still hot.
Cool.
Take can of milk from freezer. Beat on high for 5 to 6 minutes.
Fold in with cooked cooled mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
Be sure congealed before cutting.
A cool dessert for summer.

title: foiled pot roast(method:  foil)
directions: Sear both sides of roast over hot coals.
Place in a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Add sliced potatoes, onions, carrots and any other vegetables.
Season.
Seal in double foil.
Cook on hot coals about 1 hour; turn occasionally.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of sugar, crushed pretzels and melted oleo. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: lake's shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in bacon drippings.
Add stewed tomatoes and sliced whole skinless tomatoes, garlic and spices.
Add 1/2 cup water and let simmer for at least 20 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Serve over hot, white rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (add no salt).
Skin and debone.
Reserve 2 cups chicken broth.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place half of chicken.
Mix 1 cup chicken broth and cream of chicken soup. Pour over chicken. Put remaining chicken on top of soup.
Take the other cup of broth and mix with the cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over the next chicken layer.
(If you are using mushrooms, use half each time with chicken layers.)
Melt butter and mix with the stuffing.
Put over top of second soup layer.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, cooking oil and water; mix.
Add eggs; mix.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.

title: crab english muffins
directions: Cream butter and cheese in bowl.
Add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in crab meat.
Spread mixture over toasted halves of muffins.
Place on cookie sheet.
(You can now freeze well wrapped until needed.)
Heat oven and bake until hot. Cut in quarters to serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Roll chicken in margarine.
Roll in mixture of bread crumbs and cheese.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes until crispy and browned.
Serves 4.

title: fried tofu
directions: To
Make
Sauce:
Boil	the
dashi
broth with carrots, celery and
onion
until	the vegetables are tenderly cooked. Add soy sauce and thicken it with a little cornstarch (about 1 1/2 tablespoons) mixed with about 2 tablespoons water.

title: roasted root vegetable soup
directions: Place the vegetables, broth, 2 cups of water and celery seeds in a soup pot and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cover loosely and reduce heat to simmer until vegetables are very tender, 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside to cool. Transfer the vegetable mixture to a food processor and puree until very smooth. This may have to be done in batches. Return the soup to the pot. Add salt and pepper to taste and cook over medium heat until just heated through. Taste and adjust the seasonings, if necessary. Serve garnished with parsley.

title: lemon torte
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together until stiff.
On brown paper or parchment lined cookie sheet, shape meringue into shells, either with pastry bag or spoon. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until thick; take off stove and add lemon juice, coconut and butter.
Blend well.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Add meringue made with the 2 egg whites.

title: banana chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add bananas and half of flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts; then rest of flour.
Drop on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake for about 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes a soft cookie and a large batch.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sausage, cheeses, salad dressing, olives and pepper.
Grease mini muffin tin and line with wonton wrapper.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until brownish. Remove from tins, place on cookie sheet and fill with mixture. Bake until bubbly.

title: mountain mama
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and pecans.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, chicken broth and tomatoes; set aside.
Oil a 3-quart casserole.
Layer half of tortilla pieces, half of chicken, half of onion and half of cheese in the casserole.
Pour half of chicken broth mixture over layers.
Repeat layers of tortillas, chicken and onion, then pour remaining chicken broth over top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shirley's christmas candy
directions: Beat melted chocolate and peanut butter together.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Add peanuts and mix well. Add marshmallows. Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture forms a ball. Knead lightly until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well in large
bowl.
Cover
and
put in refrigerator.
Keeps for a
week.
Spoon
batter
into
greased muffin tins.
Do not wait for them to rise.
Bake at about 400° until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.
If
you want to bake some as soon as you make them, they do
not
have
to be refrigerated first. Bake a few or as many as you choose at one time and put remaining batter back in refrigerator.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage and pepperoni pizza "pie"(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fry sausage in heavy medium skillet over medium heat until cooked through, turning occasionally. Drain.
Dice sausage.
Dust one side of pie crust with 1 teaspoon of flour.
Gently transfer crust into pan.
Arrange half of Mozzarella over bottom of crust.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over Mozzarella.
Sprinkle half of Jack cheese atop sauce. Drizzle 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over cheese.
Repeat layering with remaining Mozzarella, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, remaining Jack cheese, pepperoni and sausage.
Sprinkle with olives and drizzle with remaining 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.
Top with remaining pie crust.
Pinch edges of crust together to seal.
Crimp edges to make decorative border.
Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Let pie stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: caramel rolls(made with frozen bread dough.)
directions: These light, tender sweet rolls feature a rich caramel topping made with brown sugar and heavy cream.

title: mocha-almond pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chocolates, margarine or butter and instant coffee in a large, microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High (100% power) for 2 minutes, until margarine is melted.
Remove from oven; stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from the center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk. Pour peaches in margarine.
Add sugar mixture.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, along with all the other ingredients.
Pour into loaf or mold pan and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or celery.
"Excellent with Triscuits."

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Use any desired salad dressing (optional).
Very good.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles and put into greased casserole. Sprinkle noodles over casserole. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork chops and hash browns
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Sprinkle pork chops with seasoning salt and brown in hot skillet. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine soup, sour cream, black pepper, potatoes and cheese. In 9 x 13 baking dish, layer potato mixture with pork chops on top. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Cover with onion rings and return to oven for 5 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel and thinly slice apples and fill a crock-pot.
Cook on low 18 hours.
Stir and mash, using an electric mixer.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook 4 hours longer on low.
Put in clean hot jars and seal.
Makes about 9 cups of apple butter.

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, butter, salt, vanilla and egg.
Add the buttermilk-soda mixture with flour to first mixture.
Mix just enough to be able to handle the dough.
Roll out and cut. Sprinkle with sugar; place on cookie sheets.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cut 36 large marshmallows in half.
Combine all ingredients except marshmallows and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.
Put marshmallows on center of cookies and bake 2 minutes longer.
Cool and frost if desired.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions; let set. Whisk. Add can of crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip the cream. Add to Jell-O mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Stir together and cook in crock-pot or oven for 4 hours at 275°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ginger dipping sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: pinwheel coffee cake
directions: Sift flour and measure out 3 cups.
Scald milk in small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening. Cool until lukewarm.
Pour water into bowl; sprinkle yeast in and stir until dissolved.

Add lukewarm mixture and eggs; mix well. Add flour 1/2 cup at a time, until mixture is a soft pliable ball. Sprinkle remaining flour on board and knead mixture until firm. Place in greased bowl and cover with dish towel.
Keep in a warm place and let rise until double in bulk.
Put back on floured board and knead.
Make 3 balls of dough the same size.
Add fruits and nuts at this point.
Make balls into long cones.
Place side by side and braid as hair.
Place in a greased bread pan.
Let rise again for approximately 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Make a glaze of milk and powdered sugar; drizzle over coffee cake while still warm.

title: fruit cocktail upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add salt, baking powder and sift again.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Then melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in pan or baking dish.
Add brown sugar and smooth over sides and bottom of pan.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients, but do not overmix.
Cook on a greased griddle.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan, rice, onion, green pepper, pork chops and consomme.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until liquid is cooked away.

title: baby meat balls
directions: Mix eggs, onion and 1/2 package seasoning in blender.
Add to beef and mix well.
Roll in meat balls the size of a large marble. Put in shallow pan and bake until they are cooked through.
Put tomato sauce in pan with the other half of seasoning; heat.
As the meat balls are cooked, put them in tomato sauce and cook as long as you want to cook down the sauce.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs. Spoon into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat milk until hot, but not boiling.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar and salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring all the time.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour into a baking pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour, or until a knife stuck in the center comes out clean.

title: greek-style yogurt
directions: Dissolve the milk powder in the milk and simmer 5 minutes. Pour into a heatproof bowl and let cool until you can just dip your finger into it.
Add the yogurt and stir.
Cover the bowl with plastic wrap; wrap it in a thick towel and leave it in a warm place for 5 to 6 hours.
Alternatively, you can make the yogurt in a wide-necked vacuum bottle.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water.
Brown hamburger and onion. Add seasonings, rice and soup.
Drain zucchini well.
In large casserole place 1/2 of the zucchini, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 shredded cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and flour until smooth.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up, a little bit at a time, until it is all mixed in and smooth.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: vanilla crescents
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and almonds in a food processor.
Cut in the butter.
Turn the mixture onto a pastry board and quickly knead into a smooth ball.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: laham be-ajeen(meat on pasta)
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Let rise for about one hour (follow package instructions).
Form and cut dough into disks of about 2-inches in diameter and 2-inches thick.
Grease your fingertips with the olive oil.
Press each dough piece into 1/2-inch thick disks.
Place dough disks in a lightly greased baking sheet about 2-inches apart. Set aside in a warm place.
Mix lamb (or beef), onion, green pepper, tomato, tomato sauce, Tahini, spice and salt.
Spread one to two tablespoons of the meat mixture on the dough disks.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until dough is golden brown.
Let cool for few minutes then transfer to a platter.
Serve warm or cold.

title: bran loaf
directions: Mix cereal, raisins, brown sugar and milk well and let stand for 1 hour or longer.
Then add the flour and baking powder.
Put in a small, greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or less, until done.
When cool, refrigerate.
Doubles well.

title: vegetable squares
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls; gently pat into rectangle on cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool on wire rack.
Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, stir together the cream cheese, salad dressing and dill weed or basil.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over the cooled crust.
Sprinkle with desired chopped vegetables and shredded cheese.
Gently press vegetables and cheese into the cream cheese mixture.
Chill 1 hour before cutting into squares.

title: banana-praline muffins
directions: In a small bowl, stir together brown sugar, sour cream and the pecans and set aside.
To the bananas, add egg, sugar and oil. Stir until well blended.
Add Bisquick, stirring just until moistened.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients. Mix well.

title: hot or cold baked potato salad
directions: Bake potatoes on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally while baking so they don't stick.
Add all other ingredients in bowl and stir together.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttery crunchy microwave fish fillets
directions: Pour butter over single layer of fish in a 10-inch Corning Ware or any microwavable dish.
Pour lemon juice over fish. Sprinkle with parsley and all of the Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Rotate dish and cook 6 more minutes on High.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Smooth beans on large plate.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Add additional seasoning to your taste, mild or strong.
Layer all over beans.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, all by layering.
(Kids love this dip.)

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade concentrate.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
Place in large punch bowl with two trays of ice cubes or a molded ice ring.
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly pour in chilled ginger ale.
Makes 25 servings.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery.
Add ground turkey and brown.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, soups and water.
Add chow mein noodles.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom-macaroni casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil in large Dutch oven; stir in macaroni.
Return to a rapid boil and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Rinse in cold water.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, soup, mayonnaise, cheese and mushrooms.
Add pimentos.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter. Sprinkle evenly over macaroni mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Lightly beat eggs, sugar and oil. Add mixture to dry mixture. Fold in zucchini, vanilla and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan. Check with toothpick.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in shortening.
Mix all in bowl with whisk; reserve 2 ounces of the cheese.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate; bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread remaining cheese on top; bake 5 minutes more.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk.
Let come to a hard boil. Boil 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to cool, then add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat until it loses its gloss and starts to get hard. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: caramel icing
directions: Put brown sugar, butter and milk in saucepan; cook on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil 5 minutes.
Let cool 2 minutes.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add confectioners sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla and more milk if needed.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, combine milk and lemon juice; mix well. Stir in the pineapple, cranberry sauce,
banana, marshmallows, and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Freeze overnight. Cut into squares. Makes 12-16 servings.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together; add water.
Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Add margarine.
Serve over plain cake, hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut 1 large steak in cubes and flour. Brown in oil. Add onion and garlic; brown slightly. Add mushrooms, soup and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer until done; cool 20 minutes.
Add about 1/4 cup sour cream. Serve on noodles. Serves 4.

title: daiquiri fruit salad
directions: In large saucepan, bring liquid to boiling.
Stir in gelatin to dissolve.
Remove from heat; stir in limeade concentrate and rum.
Using wire whisk or electric mixer, blend in mayonnaise. Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in pineapple, whipped cream and bananas.
Spoon into 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Recipe may be halved for 6-cup fluted tube pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: *(You can use hash browns instead of O'Brien potatoes, but add 1/2 cup of minced onion.)

title: oat bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch squares. Refrigerate 1 hour and enjoy!

title: ellen's boiled cookies
directions: Mix milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on buttered wax paper. Cool.

title: italian pasta salad with salami
directions: In shaker or jar, mix light-tasting olive oil, fresh or frozen lemon juice, garlic (minced fine), parsley flakes, dried basil, salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain, rinse in cold water and drain again.
Seed green, red and yellow peppers and slice into small chunks.
Cut salami into cubes. Slice pepperoni lengthwise, then crosswise in thin slices.
Cut cheese (preferably part skim) in bite-sized cubes.

title: coconut pie(very old recipe)
directions: Stir constantly over boiling water until thickened,about 8 minutes. Cool. Whip 1 cup cream. Pour cooled custard mixture into whipped cream. Pour into meringue pie shell.
Be sure all pockets of meringue are filled. Let stand in refrigerator several hours. Serve with fresh strawberries or any seasonable fruit.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: In blender, puree raspberries, sugar and Grand Marnier or orange juice.

title: finger jello
directions: Stir gelatine into cold water.
Stir jello (any flavor) into boiling water.
Combine both mixtures into pan, about 10 x 12-inch.
Chill, then slice.
May be eaten like cookie.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Saute onions with butter and margarine.
Put 1/2 into bottom of dish.
Layer macaroni, cheese and potatoes (2 layers).
Top with rest of onion mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: puff pastry
directions: Mix everything together.
Chill for several hours or overnight. Roll out dough into a thin rectangle.
Spread jar of mincemeat over 1/2 rectangle.
Add nuts, if desired.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Make slits across top of roll.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 350°; then for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and cut up margarine, let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350 for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: sunshine barbecue chicken
directions: You will need 1 large size Reynolds oven bag (14 x 20-inch).

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes or use sliced or diced leftovers.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Boil 2 sticks cinnamon, cloves and 2 cups apple cider.
Boil spices for 15 minutes.
Strain spices and add 1/2 can frozen orange juice to remaining hot cider and serve.

title: chicken in carrot and mushroom sauce
directions: Brown chicken in oil and remove from pan.
Add mushrooms and carrots and cook until tender.
Mix in soup and sherry, scraping bottom of pan.
Put chicken back into pan and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Put in pan.
Top with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Top with cobbler dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mike's and other's famous chili
directions: Fry ground sirloin, 1 onion, 1 stalk celery and chili powder in skillet until almost done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Then mix in crock-pot with rest of ingredients.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions, bell pepper, garlic and parsley in butter until tender.
Add crabmeat and saute for approximately 20 minutes.
Soak bread in milk.
Add this to crab mixture and stir.
Cut off heat and add beaten eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste and stir.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat mushroom soup and water on stove until warm. Add chicken breasts; bake 30 minutes on each side.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, simmer tomatoes, onion, bay leaf, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes.
Put through food mill and set aside.
In same saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly stir in tomato mixture.

title: raisin, apple or oat bran muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins or use paper liners.
Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix other ingredients together except yogurt.
Mix with oat mixture.
Stir in yogurt.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: overnight green salad
directions: Spread half of lettuce in 2-quart casserole.
Add celery, onions, green pepper and peas as second layer.
Use remaining lettuce as top layer. Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, fry 1/2 pound of bacon very crisp and crumble; sprinkle over top of salad.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Add eggs, mix thoroughly.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: creamy cheese potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups corn flake crumbs, which have been mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Mixture will be dry, so you may need to use your hands to knead together well.
Shape mixture into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken angelo
directions: Place half the mushrooms in a 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Dip chicken into beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown both sides of chicken in skillet.
Place chicken on top of mushrooms.
Arrange remaining mushrooms on chicken and top with cheese.
Add chicken broth to pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Serve chicken over hot cooked rice or noodles with chopped fresh parsley.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni and eggs until done. Pour into bowl to cool; add eggs, onion, tomato and cucumber.
Mix.

title: kahlua mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks and 2 tablespoons Kahlua in a 3-quart microwave-safe dish. Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until slightly thickened and color lightens. Cook egg yolk mixture on Medium-high power 3 to 4 minutes until thickened. Stir every 45 seconds. Set dish in a bowl of cold water.
Beat until thick, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Using an electric mixer, cream butter.	Gradually add brown sugar, mixing well. Mix in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add flour mixture gradually, blending until smooth.	Add vanilla flavoring.	Spread batter into a greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into bars and enjoy.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix melted margarine, oil and sugar.
Beat eggs and combine with water, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add both flours and baking soda.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Beat together butter, sugars and egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and half of chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 22 to 28 minutes. Immediately sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes or until chips are glassy and sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Pat into a 5 1/2 cup ring mold; unmold in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Combine catsup, sugar and mustard; spread over meat.
Return to oven for 10 minutes. Serves approximately 6.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine all solid ingredients in greased loaf pan.
Cover with liquid and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown meat.
Chop pepper and onion; add to meat and cook until tender.
Add chili powder, black pepper and salt.
Add soup and corn; simmer 15 minutes.

title: valentine pie
directions: Prepare crumb crust (1 1/2 cups crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Chill slightly.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat bananas into cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in Jell-O.
Chill until thick, stirring occasionally.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Press half into bottom of 12 x 7-inch dish.
When Jell-O mixture is partially set, whip milk.
Add lemon juice.
Beat until stiff.
Beat Jell-O mixture slightly and fold into whipped milk.
Pour in dish. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and banana slices.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Immediately add next 3 ingredients.
Mix gently, then add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cake may be frosted while warm.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt on medium heat.
Leave until it starts to boil.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate bits and vanilla until all blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Finally cut into your favorite size bites.

title: egg salad-cheese spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; season with salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
This spread can be used on your favorite bread, rolls or crackers.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter;
add Eagle
Brand
milk
and chips over low heat until chips are melted.
Pour into cooled, buttered pan or platter immediately.
Let cool
for 2 hours and cut into 2-inch squares. Store in
tightly
closed container to prevent drying out.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour 1/2 c. butter into bundt pan (for best results, do not use Teflon coated).
Baste stem and sides well.
Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle appr. 1/2 c. sugar mixture in bottom of bundt pan.
Roll each piece of biscuit in sugar and cinnamon mix and drop into pan.
After each layer of biscuits, sprinkle additional sugar mixture.
After you've placed all of the biscuit pieces in the pan, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Pour 1/2 c. of butter over biscuits.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: crunchy kisses
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Blend well.
Pour over corn flakes in large mixing bowl.
Stir lightly until covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread and stir. Add cheese and sausage.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Allow to stand a few minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: vegetable stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil green peppers.
Stuff peppers with vegetable mixture. Place in baking dish and pour tomato soup and vinegar over peppers.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Dice and fry bacon until crisp.
Add to drippings, diced apple, diced green pepper and diced onion.
Saute until tender. Add 2 large cans of Hunt's small red beans (drain before adding). Add 1 large can of chopped up tomatoes.
Add curry powder and brown sugar.
Mix together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover; set overnight.
Before serving, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as usual.
Set aside.
Saute celery and onions in butter.
Melt Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix together and spoon in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: apple surprise shurdel
directions: Pour pears into pan (with juice).
Pour in apple pie filling. Spread evenly.
Pour in cake mix and sprinkle ginger.
Cover top with butter.
Cover butter with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients.
Place remaining ingredients in jar. Pour liquid into jars and close tightly.
Refrigerate for 3 weeks.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into
dry ingredients.
Put egg into a 1 cup measure.
Beat the	egg and fill the cup with water.
Pour into a well
made	in
the
shortening and flour mixture.	Mix only enough to form
a ball.
The mixture will seem too moist, but you will be
adding
flour as you roll the pie crust.
Use what you need and freeze the rest.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: This makes one pie.

title: oh suzanna pie
directions: Mix together milk and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Put margarine and coconut in skillet and lightly brown.
Mix in 2 cups of nuts. Sprinkle on top of pie mixture. Melt caramel in microwave and drizzle all over pies. Makes 3 pies.

title: mama's yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In pan, put sugar, shortening, milk and salt; heat and stir until dissolved.
Pour into large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Add yeast and eggs.
Beat good and stir in about 3 cups flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° or 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until done.

title: biscuits "good"
directions: Sift self-rising flour into bowl.
Make hole in middle.
Add soda, buttermilk and shortening.
Mix with hand all this, stirring in flour as needed, to right consistency.
Squeeze up between index finger and thumb.

title: diane's squash
directions: Cut up and peel squash.
Cut up 2 apples.
Mix and pour over oleo, brown sugar, mace and salt.
Bake until done.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar and egg. Stir in buttermilk. Combine dry ingredients and add. Stir in pecans, dates and cherries. Chill. Drop teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Top with pecan half. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixture should be very moist but not soupy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch or larger baking dish. Place into non-preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: cinnamon-cheese toast
directions: In a small bowl, mix cottage cheese with sweetener and cinnamon.
Spread on toast.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon salad
directions: Make jello as usual according to the directions on the box.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Empty spaghetti sauce mix into saucepan; add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Heat, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in a large bowl and add Ricotta or cottage cheese, spinach, salt and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Lightly grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with a little sauce.
Layer noodles, 1/2 of cheese/spinach mixture, 1/2 of Mozzarella and 1/2 of tomato sauce mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with lightly greased foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until noodles are tender. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer in a casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with a layer of graham crackers.
Top this layer with pudding mix.
Continue layering crackers and pudding mix, ending with a layer of crackers.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange banana slices over crust.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk and add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place rhubarb in pastry shell.
Blend together sugar, tapioca, salt, egg and sour cream.
Pour over the rhubarb.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 45 minutes.
Filling should be firm and lightly browned.
It makes a lot of filling and so requires a deep dish.

title: date cookies
directions: Mix together and blend well butter, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Add salt, baking soda, vanilla, flour, dates and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: squash dressing
directions: Grate squash and onion on large section of grater.
Mix all other ingredients, except margarine, in a 375° oven.
Place a slightly greased iron skillet or casserole dish in oven until almost smoking hot.
(It is very important to do it this way or it will not brown properly.)
Remove from oven and pour melted margarine over top.
Cook until brown, (375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: yummy fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits together.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Eat and enjoy.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Run water over cobs to take off last of the chaff.
In a large pan (roaster oven), cover the cobs with water and boil 30 minutes. Use a lot of water, the cobs absorb a lot.
Strain.
Stir 3 cups of the red corn liquor into a pan and add Sure-Jell.
Let this come to a boil, then add sugar.
When this comes to a hard boil, let it boil a minute or until it starts to jell.
Test by dipping fork.
The liquid collects a minute on the groves.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sugar and cheese.
Mix cheese and sugar together and sprinkle over salad.
When ready to serve, toss with mayonnaise.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and undrained pineapple.
Spread on warm cake.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour salad dressing over and mix just before serving.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix salt, zucchini and onion.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse off salt; drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add dash of green food coloring, then seal in jar.

title: southern fried apples
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Wash, core and slice apples in 1/2-inch slices.
Heat butter in heavy skillet.
Add apple rings and one half the sugar mixture; cook about 3 minutes. Turn, sprinkle with remainder of sugar mixture and continue cooking until apples are almost transparent.
Serve hot; makes 6 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Fry hamburg; add the beans and taco seasoning.
Put in 8 x 8-inch frypan and top with sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.
Makes 10 - 12 servings.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Season with pinch of rosemary, salt and pepper.
Drain!
Buy Pepperidge Farm puff pastry, 2 sheets per package, and thaw.
Cut in quarters.
Take 1 quarter, roll out a little to cover chicken breast.
Set breast in center (drain on paper towels first).
Sprinkle small amount chopped green onion over top.
Take cream cheese, slice chunks size of butter patty and spread on chicken.
Fold pastry and seal (pinch).
Heat oven to 450°.
Put chicken in and immediately turn to 400°.
Cook until golden brown, about 1/2 hour.
Serve with Mushroom Sauce.

title: sweet shop pudding(serves 4)
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Stir in candy just before serving.

title: key lime meringue pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake pie crust at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Stir together sweetened condensed milk and lime juice until blended.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Chill 8 hours.

title: chocolate delight(refrigerate)
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° for 15 minutes in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first five ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a baked graham cracker crust.
Freeze at least two hours before cutting.
Wrap and store in freezer.
To serve, you may sprinkle some chopped nuts on top if desired.

title: grandma's zucchini bread
directions: Dates and nuts may be left out.
Raisins may be added in their place also.

title: grannie's german steak roll-up
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on steak.
Thinly spread mustard on top.
On top of steak, layer the following:
bacon strips, onions and mushrooms.
Roll up steak and pin together with toothpicks. Grease or spray pan.
Sprinkle flour on top of steak for crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot swiss tuna(microwave)
directions: Split hamburger buns.
Combine tuna, cheese, celery, mayonnaise, catsup and lemon juice.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Divide tuna mixture among 4 buns.
Wrap each sandwich in waxed paper and twist ends of paper.
Cook one at a time 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until rolls are hot.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: Put turkey carcass pieces in large kettle and cover with water. Cover kettle and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Skim surface to remove excess fat.
Add vegetables and salt and simmer 15 minutes.
Add noodles and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cabbage crunch(chinese salad)
directions: Break noodles into small pieces.
Noodles and almonds may be toasted, if desired.
Place noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds in a plastic bag or sealable container.
Combine sugar, vegetable oil, vinegar and Soy sauce
and mix well to make dressing. Combine ingredients immediately prior to serving as it will not keep, the dry ingredients get soggy.

title: baba's favorite cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
With electric mixer cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and blend well.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.

title: orange cream cheese salad
directions: Combine oranges and juice, apricot jello and Knox gelatine in saucepan; heat.
Add cream cheese which has been cut into cubes and mix.
Cool slightly.
Fold in Cool Whip (reserve some Cool Whip for topping).
Place in slightly oiled pan (9 x 12 x 2-inch). Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Cut into squares and top with Cool Whip and orange segments.
Serve on lettuce leaf with sprig of mint or sprig of watercress.

title: scripture cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: catfish
directions: Mix cornmeal with Cajun seasoning.
Dip catfish into mixture of milk, eggs and mustard.
Coat well with cornmeal mixture.
Heat oil.
Drop fish into hot oil and cook until golden brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except soup, and make into meatballs.
Brown on baking sheet, turning over once.
Move meatballs to casserole and add mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or a little longer.
These freeze very good, so you can double batch and have ready for next batch of company.

title: standard butter cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and well beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and flour.
Add beaten egg whites, then vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: amanda's beans
directions: Combine the drained beans with enough dressing to coat and place them into a casserole dish.
Marinate them in the refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lay the bacon strips on top of the beans and cook uncovered until the beans are heated through and the bacon is crisp, about 30 minutes. This is amazingly simple by amazingly delicious!
You can also add sliced almonds, if you like.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter, cream and milk for 3 minutes.
Add the oats.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.
The cocoa may be omitted and add some peanut butter.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Save out 1 cup corn chips and mix remaining chips with other ingredients.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Spread top with 1 cup sour cream, an additional 1/2 cup shredded cheese and circle with reserved corn chips around edge.
Bake an additional 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot-n-quick artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium-high (70%) 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until hot.
Serve warm with thin slices French bread or rye crackers, if desired.

title: pecan wafers
directions: Cover large cookie sheet with foil; grease with vegetable shortening.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to directions.
While they are cooking, mix in a bowl the soup, milk and drained tuna.
Drain cooked noodles.
Add tuna mixture and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vinegar sauce for cut up vegetables
directions: Bring to a good boil.
Store in gallon glass jar.
Cool and store.
Put over cut up fresh vegetables or bean salad.
Keeps for a long time.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Beat together until creamy the butter, brown sugar and egg. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cracks are dry.
Use loaf pan, greased and floured.

title: easy-do sweet dough
directions: Measure water into large mixer bowl.
Blend well.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer. By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Toss dough over lightly floured surface until no longer sticky.
Knead 1 minute.
Shape.

title: cucumber and yogurt dip
directions: Scrub cucumber to remove wax.
Grate the unpeeled cucumber and drain very well until almost dry.
Combine with other ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese to a soft dough.
Drop by the spoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Mix melted butter or margarine with the garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flours together and add alternately with milk and flavoring.
Bake for 1 hour and 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes a large cake.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Run cold water over macaroni and let cool.
Add green pepper, onion and celery seed.
Make dressing with mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Stir until mayonnaise is smooth.
Pour over macaroni and mix well.
If macaroni is dry, make more dressing.
Best if refrigerated.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze together. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together. Break 1/2 angel food cake in pieces and place in a 9 x 13 pan. Cover with 1/2 Cool Whip mixture. Then cover with 1/2 strawberry mixture. Repeat again.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon half and half.
Whisk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup of half and half into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Blend well.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and nuts.

title: nachos
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and salsa.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over tortilla chips.
Top with tomatoes, green onions, olives and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation Time: 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and put into water with the lemon juice to keep them from turning brown.
(Use any good cooking apple; we use Granny Smith apples, as they cook done easily.)
Red or Gold Delicious do not do well in this recipe.

title: turkey stuffing(moist)
directions: Soak bread almost two days old in milk until soft.
Press out all the moisture and add an equal amount of quickly cooked hoe cakes or corn bread.
Place in saucepan with onion, butter and bacon.
Cook 10 minutes without browning.
When cold, season with salt and pepper, celery seed and minced parsley.
Use sage and thyme and the yolk of 1 egg.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll roll mix and press flatly onto cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix together cream cheese, salad dressing and dill weed in mixing bowl until smooth.
Spread onto top of cooled roll mix.
Cut into squares.
Place assorted vegetables on top.
Sprinkle cheese over top of vegetables.
Place olive, if desired, on top of each pizza square.
Keep refrigerated until use.
Recipe can be easily doubled.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: In a large pan (frying pan), fry cut up bacon until crisp. Drain off grease.
Pour in wine and simmer.
Meanwhile, as bacon is simmering, cook the spaghetti.
Then mix eggs and cheese together in a mixing bowl.
When spaghetti is ready, drain and return to pan.
Add the cheese and egg mixture, covering the spaghetti.
Mix thoroughly.
Finally, add wine and bacon mixture; mix thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: egg rolls from thailand
directions: Chop all (except pastry squares and egg) ingredients and stir fry. Drain off any grease. Fill center of pastry squares; fold up bottom and sides then roll up; seal with a beaten egg. Fry in hot corn oil.

title: salsa
directions: *Stewed tomatoes or diced are really the best.

title: aunt minnie's crisp cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, water and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Roll out on floured board; cut.
Sprinkle on decorative sugars, if desired.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Cookies should be golden brown.
Cool.
Frost if desired.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken, stirring constantly. Add half and half, parsley, crab meat, chives, sherry, Old Bay and salt.
Mix well.
Heat just to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients in a serving bowl.
Toss with desired amount of dressing and serve.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Combine fruit, tapioca and grape juice in a crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover (about 3 cups).
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 or 10 hours.
Before serving, stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm or cold as a soup or dessert.
Makes 10 to 12 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bell pepper and onion. Cook and drain macaroni. Mix all together real good. Put in casserole dish. Place in oven for about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is real bubbly.

title: ham salad
directions: Buy a small ham (Bryan, Gooch), about 2 to 3 pounds.
I usually buy a ham and serve with rice salad.
A couple of days later, take leftover ham and make a ham salad and if I have even more, I make a ham and cheese pie (recipe included in cookbook).

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place one cake layer or one-half of 9 x 13-inch cake in bottom of a 1 gallon or larger punch bowl.
(I use Tupperware cake box because I make 2 round layers.)
Cover with 1/2 of instant vanilla pudding, 1/2 can cherry pie filling, 1/2 can of fruit cocktail, 1/2 pineapple and coconut and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil the Chicken, then remove all bones and skin.
Tear meat into chunks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: For 10 minutes cook broccoli, onion and celery.
Drain; put in a baking dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup, cooked rice, Cheez Whiz and jalapeno Cheez Whiz.
Mix together and bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Then mix stuffing with butter and spread over the top.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes until the top is a light golden brown.

title: wheat germ cookies
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients	together
in
a small bowl.
In another
bowl, beat egg.
Add cooled margarine, molasses, milk and wheat germ.
Add dry ingredients.	Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart
on
lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put into casserole dish in layers:
soup diluted with 3/4 cup water, noodles, chicken and celery.
Garnish with mandarin oranges and cashew nuts.
(Can put cashews throughout if desired.)
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 (six times the amount serves 40).

title: stella adamek's rye bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine next 3 ingredients in a cup and add to dry ingredients.
Work in 9 cups white flour.
Place on floured board and knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased container and let raise to double the size.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan; melt almond bark (all but one square) and chocolate chips on low heat until melted.
Take off heat and add marshmallows, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Pour into pizza pan, spread out to sides and sprinkle with coconut.
Cut cherries in half and arrange on top.
Melt one square of almond bark and drizzle over top.
Looks like pizza!
Cut in small wedges and serve.

title: pizza burger
directions: Grind bologna, cream cheese and Colby cheese through a food grinder alternately.
In a bowl mix ground-up mixture, Mozzarella cheese, oregano and pizza sauce.
Spread on open face buns.
Place face up in oven or under broiler and heat until bubbly.

title: pea casserole
directions: Cook and drain the peas.
Add water chestnuts, mushroom soup and pimentos, chopped fine.
Saute celery, onions and green pepper in oleo.
Add this mixture to the pea mixture.
Pour into two greased casserole dishes.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Put crushed potato chips on top and heat.

title: mama's beets
directions: Cook until thick and pour over beets.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for a filled, one-crust pie, using 9-inch pie pan or 9-inch quiche pan. Heat oven to 400°. Layer Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese in pie crust lined pan.
Top with pepperoni and mushrooms.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in separate bowl.
Add flour mixture to shortening mixture about a cup at a time. This recipe does not have to be refrigerated.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all 4 ingredients in an electric blender until very smooth.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups or an amount equal to a 14 ounce can.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: knox blox shapes
directions: You will need cookie cutters to shape.
