title: green bean delight
directions: Drain 1/2 the water of green beans, put the rest of the water and beans into a medium saucepan.
Add the can of soup.
Cook over medium heat (about 10 minutes).
Add cheese to desired taste. Cook until cheese makes a creamy sauce over the green beans.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook onions until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add 2 tablespoons bacon drippings to softened cream cheese.
Add onion and crumbled bacon.
Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Stuff mushrooms with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put butter in an 8 x 8-inch square Pyrex pan in oven at 350° to 375° to melt.
Then mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder together.
Pour over butter, then add fruit (any type of fruit filling will do).
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburg lasagna cheese bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with tomato sauce and spices.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream with diced green pepper and diced scallions.
Layer over egg noodles.
Spread in greased pan 1/2 egg noodles, 1/2 sauce and hamburger, then cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool, cut and enjoy!

title: chicken oriental(broiled or grilled)
directions: Place chicken on grill or rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of sauce.
Grill or broil about 10 minutes, turn and brush remaining sauce and broil or grill for 10 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: couscous with chickpeas and feta cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, bring broth to boil.
Stir in couscous. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Transfer couscous to large bowl and fluff with fork.
Let stand 5 minutes; fluff again. mix in chickpeas, scallions, cheese and olives.
Pour dressing over mixture and toss lightly with fork.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Serves 6. Enjoy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: octopus casserole
directions: Boil octopus slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender when pierced. Rinse off black covering.
Cut up octopus into bite size pieces. Cut up both cheeses into bite size pieces.
Toss all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Season to taste.
Pour small amount of oil over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: ground beef relish patties
directions: Mix the ground beef with the salt, pepper and parsley.
Shape mixture into 8 patties, 4-inch diameter.

On each of 4 patties, arrange an onion ring, a tomato slice and a slice of cheese. Cover with the other 4 patties and press edges together to seal. Broil on both sides for a total of about 20 minutes.

title: pheasant
directions: Wash pheasant well. Salt and pepper. Line Dutch oven with tin foil and place bird in center. In a bowl, mix wine, marmalade, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour over bird. Cut butter in squares and put on and around bird. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste every 20 minutes. Tighten foil after each basting.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with dampened paper towels and remove stems. Pour some oil in a bowl.
With fingers, wipe oil on outside of each mushroom cap.
Add a drop of oil to the center of the inside.
Chop stems fine and combine them in a bowl with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and cheese; toss together.
Add onion, chervil (or tarragon), salt and dash of pepper.
Toss again.
Add milk or stock.
Lightly mix. Mixture should be moist enough to hold together.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels. Crumble and set aside.
Place onion rings, garlic powder, mustard, brown sugar and vinegar in a large skillet. Cover and cook 20 minutes over medium heat. Combine beans in 3-quart casserole.
Stir in bacon and onion mixture, blending ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Partially cool.
Add margarine and stir.
Add Salad Supreme and stir.
Marinate overnight.
Add cucumber, tomatoes and salad dressing.
Stir and ready to serve.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Add beef cubes to marinade, turning to coat.
Refrigerate 24 to	36
hours
to
give
marinade time to tenderize the beef; turn the
meat occasionally.
Fill skewers, alternating meat cubes with
mushroom caps or other kabobs tidbits of your choice.
Place skewers
4	to
inches from the heat.
Broil about 25
minutes, turning
frequently and basting often with marinade.
About last 5 minutes of cooking, add small tomatoes to ends of skewers.

title: tomato and squash pie
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into greased 9 or 10-inch round or square pan and mix.
Next 4 ingredients beat until smooth with electric mixer and then beat for 1 minute.
Put this into the dish and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: flourless (soft) peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool before removing from baking sheet.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: pineapple rum sauce
directions: In large bowl, combine brown sugar and rum; mix until combined.
Add pineapple; toss gently to combine.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a large, heavy saucepan; blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken, peas and carrots and seasonings; heat.

title: baked cinnamon apples
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil. Add cinnamon candy. Stir until it melts. Pour over cored apples. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Dip syrup over apples when finished.

title: grandma kirby's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage (294°) on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts; cook to amber color.
Add soda; stir. Add vanilla and butter.
Pour onto greased marble slab.
Cool and break.
Store in airtight container.

title: luncheon sandwichlobster or crabmeat
directions: Mix cream cheese with the juice of the fish.
Add the other ingredients.
Spread on the rusks.
Top with tomato slice and slice of processed cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, about 25 minutes at 300°.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Stir in chocolate; add eggs.
Beat, one at a time, for 3 to 5 minutes (after adding each egg).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Let chill for 2 hours or freeze.

title: meat pie
directions: In a skillet, put stew meat and blade meat.
Cook until light brown.
Together mix meat and crushed crackers.
Get pie crust and put meat and crackers, cooked together, and then put it in the pie shell.
Bake at about 350° in oven for 1/2 hour.
Roll out the dough for pie crust and put on bottom of pie shell and on top of the stew meat.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla; then mix dry ingredients with shortening mixture.
Add raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: old-tyme chili pie
directions: Mix cornbread as directed.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat chili with 1/4 cup water to simmering point, spoon over cornbread batter, sprinkle grated cheese and minced onion over chili.
Bake in 425° oven 15 to 18 minutes.
Cornbread will rise above chili mixture.
Serve hot; makes 4 generous servings.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Lower heat and cook all day until thick and dark.
Stir occasionally.
Place in small jars; cool and freeze.

title: mixed vegetable tempura
directions: Pour vegetable oil at least 2-inches deep into wide skillet. Heat to 375°.
Beat the eggs with wire whisk; blend in 1/2 cup water.
Sprinkle the cake flour evenly over the liquid.
Stir in flour with whisk only until moist and large lumps disappear.
Mix the shrimp, mixed vegetables and onion into flour mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until lightly golden.

title: asparagus-cheese canapes
directions: Blend egg with cream cheese and Blue cheese.
Trim crust from bread slices; roll each slice lightly with a rolling pin.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Cut asparagus stalks length of bread; place on edge of bread.
Roll as for jelly roll; brush with margarine. Place in covered plastic container and freeze.
Remove from freezer; cut each roll crosswise in 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate and butter melt.
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Boil for 1 minute; stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Beat at high speed until spreading consistency. Immediately spread on cake.
Yield:
Will frost top and sides of one 3 layer cake.

title: pasta and mozzarella salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Toss macaroni with Dressing.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese over each serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fired up chili dip
directions: Combine chili and Ro-Tel in medium saucepan.
Heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Pour into shallow, 1 1/2-quart bowl. Arrange lettuce along outside edge to form a circle.
Continue to arrange remaining ingredients in a circular pattern in the order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chilled crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice and garlic salt well.
Spread on bottom of serving dish.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
In small bowl, mix chili sauce, ketchup, horseradish sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add to chilled dish.
Cover with backfin crabmeat and chill at least 1/2 hour.

title: favorite ham balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.

title: luau burgers
directions: Shape ground beef into patties.
Place each patty on a square of foil.
Top with pineapple ring. Fill hole with chili sauce or barbecue sauce. Wrap in foil.
Broil in oven or over charcoal until done. Serve on a bun.

title: hot potato rolls
directions: Mix shortening, milk, sugar, salt, potato and egg.
Add yeast. Add flour.
Mix.
Place in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours before using.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken in butter, remove from skillet and set aside.
Saute onion and peppers in butter until semi-tender and remove from skillet.
Return chicken to skillet, add onions and peppers, cover and simmer until chicken is done. Add cheese to skillet, cover and continue to simmer just long enough to melt cheese.
May be served with Mexican-style rice.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Peel baked potatoes or not. Mash with a fork. Melt butter in a Dutch oven pan over medium heat. Add onion and saute until tender. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Stir in potatoes, half and half, milk, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Top each bowl with cheese and bacon.

title: preserved kumquats
directions: Wash the kumquats in warm water; drain and dry.
Gently prick each kumquat with a skewer in 2 or 3 places.
Combine the water and sugar in a saucepan (not aluminum).
Bring to a boil and add the kumquats.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until syrup is thick and clear.
Stir in the ginger and lime juice.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add Cheddar cheese and dressing mix. Mix well and roll in large ball and roll in nuts.
May be frozen.

title: mom's best pecan pie(ethel greenwood chadwick)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Add syrup, salt, vanilla and nuts. Bake in 9-inch pie shell for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; slightly drain.
In the same skillet, add 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Coat zucchini in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Use 2-quart casserole dish and alternate sliced zucchini, sliced tomatoes and hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Take out and sprinkle cheeses on top and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheeses melt.

title: rich raisin bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine 2 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.
In a saucepan heat milk, water and butter until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour mixture, add eggs.
Blend on low until moistened.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in raisins and enough of the remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface for 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough and divide into 2 parts.

title: lou's gooey butter coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Blend cake mix with eggs and melted butter.
Pat evenly into lightly greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and all but 2 tablespoons of confectioners sugar.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour over batter in pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle reserved confectioners sugar on top. Return to oven and continue baking for 25 minutes longer.

title: spicy low-fat jambalaya
directions: In nonstick 12-inch skillet, heat oil on medium; saute onion and bell pepper for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce, water, ham, garlic, parsley, thyme and cayenne.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Stir.
Add bay leaves on top.
Reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Uncover; let sit 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork and serve.
Makes 2 large servings (352 calories and 4 1/2 grams fat per serving).

title: overnite cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, butter and lard or margarine together.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift salt, flour, soda and cream of tartar together, then add.
Mix well.
Form into loaves (wrapped in wax paper) and refrigerate overnite.
Chocolate bits and/or nutmeats may be added, if desired.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water or in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended. Spread into greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 mins.
Cool completely.
Add chocolate frosting if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box using half the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt in saucepan, caramels, butter and milk.
Pour over cake.
Spread the chocolate chips and pecans on top of this.
Pour the remaining cake batter over this and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Dip in melted chocolate chips (or use 1/2 choc. chips & half butterscotch chips). Cool to firm.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix together jello and pineapple (do not add water).
Heat until jello is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in large dish; sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cocktail sauce(shrimp)
directions: Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook the beets until tender.
Slip off skins.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, spices and salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the beets and simmer 5 minutes longer. Pack the beets into (hot) sterilized jars.
If not enough liquid to cover beets, add hot vinegar.
Seal immediately.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: summer mincemeat
directions: Core tomatoes and apples.
Put in food chopper.
Add ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Immediately put in jars.
Ready for pie.

title: calorie on a ritz
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Boil hard for three minutes.
Have Ritz crackers placed on a cookie sheet. Pour mixture over crackers.
Take a spoon and make sure mixture is spread well on crackers.
Put chopped nuts on top of crackers. (Nuts are to be chopped fine.) Put in a 300° oven and bake 10 minutes (preheat oven).
Remove from oven and place on aluminum foil until cool.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in an ungreased 9-inch pan. Makes three holes in the dry ingredients.
In the first hole, put the oil.
In the second hole, put the vinegar.
In the third hole, put the vanilla.
Pour the water over all and mix with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Frost right in pan or dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Cook chicken pieces in margarine at medium temperature.
When chicken pieces are browned, add picante sauce and water.
Cover and simmer until all moisture has evaporated.

title: chunky granola bars
directions: Combine egg, peanut butter and honey in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to bubble.
Remove from heat; add granola and mix well.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Cook vegetables as directed; drain.
Combine all ingredients and chill several hours.
Makes a large salad.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Place in greased casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and nuts.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy, pepper, beans and 2/3 cup onions in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir; sprinkle remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: potluck dinner
directions: In a 5-quart stockpot cook cabbage in boiling water until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add hot dogs and add pepper.
Cook until hot dogs are done.
Salt to taste.
Eat with cornbread.

title: crimson pie(a great holiday dessert)
directions: Coarsely grind orange in processor. Transfer to heavy saucepan. Add berries, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Boil over medium-high heat until thick, stirring constantly, for about 3 minutes. Cool completely.

title: german kraut
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and chili sauce to a boil.
Mix the other ingredients together and pour the hot mixture over it (do not use the juice from the vegetables).

title: pretzel salad
directions: lst Layer:
Mix together pretzels, pecans, butter and granulated sugar.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix chocolate squares and margarine in a glass bowl in microwave (about 1 1/2 minutes on high setting).
Stir mixture until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla, blending thoroughly. Stir in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Spread brownie mixture in greased 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 8 pie shaped wedges.
Serve topped with hot fudge sauce.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Pour mixture on pan evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on towel and dump cooked mixture.
Peel off wax paper.
Roll in towel long way. Cool for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven-smoked fish
directions: Cut fish into fillets.
Place fish in single layer in cake pan.
Brush both sides of fish with equal parts of soy sauce and liquid smoke.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° until desired doneness.

title: baked fudge
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Will fall after rising.

title: working girl rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over top.
Add eggs and yeast mixture; mix into flour.
Place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
To make rolls, place in greased pans.
Let rise for 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 10 days.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix well sugar, oil, eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from cob; set aside.
In 8-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble, reserving drippings.
Add corn, milk, sugar, salt and pepper to reserved drippings. Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In screw top jar shake together light cream and flour until combined, stir into corn mixture.
Add butter or margarine, cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in large pan.
Top with brown sugar, flour, 1/2 cup butter and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy tuna and rice casserole
directions: Lightly grease 8 x 8 casserole dish.
Combine rice, cheese, tuna, onion, parsley, and season-all salt.
Stir in eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish, and bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set and slightly browned on top.
Serve with tangy butter sauce.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients, add corn, bring to a boil and boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from stove and cool.
Freeze or enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken pieces until tender.
Remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cover bottom of oblong dish with chicken. Crumble crackers over chicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Set aside broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix celery and chicken soups and sour cream together.
Add chicken to mixture.
Pour in an 8 x 12-inch dish. Cover the top with stuffing mix.
Spoon some broth over the stuffing mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Cook noodles by package directions.
Serve over noodles and enjoy.

title: my best rhubarb pie(rhubarb grows like a weed, but such a tasty weed!)
directions: Place tomatoes in pie shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Mix together butter, sugar and flour; pour over tomatoes, then pour vinegar over.
Add top crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until thick.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold all ingredients together.
Spoon on 2 cookie sheets.
Cover with foil. Turn oven on to 350°, then turn off when you put cookies in. Peel cookies off the next morning!

title: cucumber salad
directions: After slicing all vegetables, place them in a bowl and pour Zesty Italian dressing over the vegetables.
Let the mixture chill for an hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg, cheese and soup mix.
Grate potatoes into bowl of water.
Place potatoes (by handfuls) on a clean dish towel and squeeze out water.
Immediately mix potatoes, cheese mixture, salt and pepper.
Add about 2 heaping tablespoons sour cream (don't make mixture too moist).
Fry pancakes in oil in nonstick pan for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: easy fruit mix
directions: Drain the juice from the oranges.
Add pineapples and juice and pudding mix.
Stir.
Add sliced bananas.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger until crumbly; add garlic, onion and celery. Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings. Blend well; cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Drain off grease. Arrange alternately noodles, cheese and sauce using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Slice top third of each loaf.
Remove bread inside each loaf, leaving about 1/2-inch shell.
Save inside of bread for bread crumbs.
Place lentils in large soup pot with 1 1/2 quarts water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Drain lentils, reserving liquid.
Puree lentils in blender, adding enough reserved liquid to make 3 cups of soup.
Return soup to pot; reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in nonstick skillet until onion is tender.
Stir into soup along with spinach, lemon juice and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until spinach wilts and soup is hot.
While soup heats, place bread bowls on baking sheets and heat in 375° oven 5 minutes or until crisp.
Ladle soup into bowls and replace bread tops.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil to melt cheese.
Serve promptly.
Serves 4.

title: tomato and shrimp salad
directions: Put tomatoes into a bowl.
Mix olive oil and lemon juice together; stir in herbs and onions.
Pour over tomatoes.
Add shrimp, combining gently.
Check for seasonings and add salt and pepper as desired.
Let stand marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes, then chill.
Serve on lettuce, sprinkle wheat germ on salad.

title: three layer jello
directions: 1st Layer:
Dissolve 2 small packages lime jello in 2 cups boiling water and 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add crushed pineapple. Let set until firm and add 2nd Layer.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Start cooking slow.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.	Stir well.
Pour into jars and seal.
Can be served over cream cheese with crackers.

title: golden creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, carrots, onions, celery, parsley, salt and pepper and water to cover vegetables.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Gradually add milk to flour mix until well blended.
Gradually add to potatoes.
Cook until thickened. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cream.
Fold in ice cream. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.

title: chinese style spareribs
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add all remaining ingredients, except spareribs.
Place ribs in large baking pan. Pour mixture over them.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, turning meat a few times.
Place ribs on rack in baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Keep egg whites in separate bowl.

title: lite lemon angel
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk; chill until firm.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
Divide pudding between layers.
May be frosted with lite Cool Whip just before serving.

title: soft gingerbread cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, mix molasses with soda until it foams.
Beat in egg and butter. Add water.
Mix ginger with flour and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 11-inch shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut in 12 squares.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Heat oven
In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients
except
potato chips.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking
pan.
Sprinkle
with
chips.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until heated through.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook rice in beef bouillon.
Saute onion.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add cream of chicken soup and cook slowly for about 30 minutes or until done.
Add sour cream.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg and salt and pepper. Add Cheddar cheese and mix well. Add macaroni. Stir until coated. Put into 2-1/2 qt. baking dish.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate rolls; pat on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes; let cool.
Mix with a mixer the cream cheese, oleo and dry Ranch dressing mix until smooth, then spread mixture on the rolls.
Add the chopped vegetables (whichever are your favorites).
Top with grated carrots and grated cheese.
Cut into bars and enjoy!

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks and jam.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating vigorously. Fold in egg whites, beaten.
Put in greased lined pan.
Use caramel icing on cake.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch glass pie dish.
Place frozen berries in bowl.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon flour; toss to coat berries.
Spoon mixture into prepared pie dish.
In medium bowl, rub remaining 1 cup flour and butter together with fingertips until coarse meal forms.
Mix in remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add milk, egg, lemon peel and vanilla; stir to blend.
Pour batter over berry mixture.
Bake pudding until firm in center and top is golden brown, about 55 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Cube cheese in 1/2-inch cubes.
Put in microwave-safe bowl. Empty Ro-Tel in blender container and blend at high speed until liquefied.
Pour over cubed cheese.
Microwave on Medium-high for 4 minutes. Let set 2 minutes and stir.
Microwave again if cheese is not melted.
Good chilled as dip or heated for nachos.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Crumble the cracklin and pour 1/2 cup hot water over them. Add this to the meal.
Use enough hot water to mix into a dough. Let stand about 5 minutes.
If dough is too stiff, add a little more water.
Shape into small pones and put into greased hot pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes according to size of pones.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break or cut up broccoli. Mix with other ingredients.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, cocoa, margarine and granulated sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; stir into mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Use unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lori's zucchini crescent pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in butter in a large frying pan over medium heat until tender.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Remove from heat.
Stir together eggs and cheese in a large bowl, then add to vegetable mixture.

title: eleanor's ginger cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, molasses and Crisco.
Cool and add eggs, spices and salt.
Add baking soda to warm water, then mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight or freeze for future use.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 10 to 15 dozen.
Easy to roll out; great for Christmas cookies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Let spinach thaw out.
Once thawed, squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator about 2 hours before serving.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell cooled eggs.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Take out yolks and put in bowl.
Break up yolks with fork.
Add all ingredients except paprika.
Mix until fluffy.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 12 deviled eggs.

title: kosher dills
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and spices, and cool.
This makes a good sauce.
Rinse kosher dills in cold water.
Pour sauce over dills that have been put in a jar.
Let stand 2 weeks in refrigerator, turning daily.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour and cornmeal in a mixing bowl.
Stir lightly, then add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 375° until done.

title: mock chicken loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Tear chicken into little pieces.
Mix all ingredients together until thoroughly combined.
Spray loaf pan with cooking spray.
Press mixture into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 90 minutes.
Turn out onto serving platter; garnish with parsley and serve.

title: applesauce cake 1
directions: Cream butter and sugar well, add eggs then applesauce.
Mix the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice.
Use some of this to dredge the raisins, nuts and dates.
Add flour and other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 3 loaf pans or 2 large tube pans at 275° about 2 hour.

title: hurry-up pie
directions: In a bowl, mix crushed pineapple with container of Cool Whip. Place mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate, then serve.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough; press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover crust with meat mixture; top with process cheese spread.
Continue baking until process cheese spreads begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place thick layer of broken Ritz crackers in an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Drizzle melted margarine over crackers.
Place bite size pieces of chicken over this.
Combine sour cream, chicken broth and cream of chicken soup; pour over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 375° oven until light brown.

title: crab regal
directions: In a 1-quart casserole or mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 2 individual casserole, sauce dishes or shells.
Cook, uncovered, 1 minute and 30 seconds or until edges bubble.
Makes 2 servings.

title: white velvet bars
directions: Layer One:
Spread unbaked pie crust in an oblong pan.

title: artichoke balls
directions: May be refrigerated up to 8 hours prior to serving.
Freezes well.
Allow 5 minutes extra cooking time if it has been chilled.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, spices and milk.
Add margarine to potatoes.
Blend with milk and egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until filling is firm.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Blend hot potatoes with butter, sour cream, salt and pepper on low speed, then on high speed until light and fluffy.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Bake at
325° for 1 hour, covered.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: creole-style flounder
directions: Saute green pepper and onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Arrange fish in a lightly greased shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over fillets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.
Calories per serving:

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving, tossing occasionally.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat the frying pan.
Add butter and brown the onion and celery.
Remove and add the rice.
Cook until brown, stirring constantly.

In a separate kettle, heat the tomatoes with the seasoning and the stock, then add the rice, onion and celery. Simmer slowly over a low fire until rice is tender, about 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally with a fork to prevent sticking.
Fifteen minutes before serving, fry the hamburg which has been shaped into small balls and add to rice.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Butter and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Melt butter and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick.
Slowly add 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in nuts, Frangelico, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until they form soft peaks.
Slowly add 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until stiff.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Put
first
three
ingredients in saucepan and boil for three minutes.
Add
remaining ingredients and stir.
Do this quickly and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes. Bake in greased and floured tube pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease an angel food or Bundt pan.
Shake biscuits in a bag with the cinnamon-sugar combination.
Put biscuits into the greased pan.
Boil the brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese (optional) and taco mix; spread on a dish.
Top with shredded lettuce, Cheddar cheese and small chunks of tomato.
Chopped onions, green peppers and black olives may be added for extra flavor.
Use nacho or tortilla chips to dip.
Serve chilled.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Place everything in large casserole with tight cover.
Stir well and several times while cooking.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a loaf pan and bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Set on platter with mashed potatoes and string beans.

title: french-style cinnamon coffee mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
For 1 cup of beverage, use 1 tablespoon to 3/4 cup boiling water.
Serve with a cinnamon stick and a dollop of whipped cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oil and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add oatmeal, vanilla, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Put in refrigerator until the dough is firm.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned, in 350° oven.
Makes 90 cookies.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil potato with peeling on until done.
Peel when done and mash potato and add a little butter while mashing with fork.
Add powdered sugar with the potato.
Pat out like biscuit dough. Spread peanut butter on the dough like you would on a sandwich. You will pat dough pretty thin because you are going to roll the dough.
After you have rolled the dough lengthwise, put in fridge until chilled, then cut into bite-sizes and put in airtight container and keep in fridge.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture; mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.
Spread Lazy Daisy Frosting (recipe follows) over top and broil as directed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: rum or bourbon balls
directions: Crush wafers fine.
Mix with chopped nuts, cocoa, corn syrup and rum until mixture forms soft paste.
Dust palms of hands with confectioners sugar.
Shape paste into balls about the size of a walnut.
Set aside one hour, then roll in sugar.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 30 balls.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat shortening and vanilla for 30 seconds.
Gradually add powdered sugar; mix well.
Add milk.
Beat in enough additional sifted powdered sugar to make a frosting of fluffy consistency.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Bake beef at 350° for four hours.
After beef is done, cut meat up in little pieces and mix all ingredients together.
Put meat back in oven for another hour and a half.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced tea
directions: Place 1 medium stick cinnamon and 1 tsp whole cloves in 3 quarts of water and bring to a boil. Simmer for about 10 minutes. Then add 6 tsp of orange pekoe tea. Let this simmer for another 5 minutes. Pour in the juice of 4 oranges and 2 lemons and 1 1/4 c. sugar and remove from fire. If mixture is not spice enough, let it simmer for a while longer.

title: penn school bar-b-que
directions: Cook stew beef; peel and dice potatoes; cook rice.
Mix all ingredients, add
onions
and season with salt and pepper. Serve with soda crackers.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and serve 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: mike's muffins
directions: Using large mixing bowl, mix together first four ingredients. Add buttermilk, eggs, sugar and oil to mixture.
Sift together flour and baking soda, then add to mixture.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine milk and salsa. Transfer to a slow cooker coated with nonstick cooking spray. Stir in cream cheese, crab, onions and chilies. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours, stirring every 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: soft sugar cakes
directions: Cream eggs, Crisco and sugar.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and cream of tartar. Add dry ingredients to rest of mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put onion in enough water to cover in large saucepan.
Boil until onions are transparent.
Check oysters for shells then add oysters with liquid to onions and boil; add canned milk and heat slowly; stirring constantly.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Add fresh milk and bring almost to a boil.
Remove from heat and serve with saltines, catsup and hot sauce, if desired.

title: cajun country pork soutache
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown pork in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat. Add cream cheese, green onion and parsley.
Stir until cheese melts.
Unroll dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Roll to 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spoon filling down center of dough, leaving 1-inch of dough on both ends and 3-inches on both sides.
Cut dough on each side into 3/4-inch strips (diagonal).
Brush egg over strips.
Lay strips alternately over filling on diagonal.
Should resemble a braid; brush dough with remaining egg.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks.
Add milk and lime juice until thick.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: oatmeal snacks
directions: Beat egg; add other liquid ingredients.
Blend thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: shoe peg marinated salad
directions: Mix all and drain in a colander.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate zucchini with skin; add flour, baking powder, Parmesan cheese, milk and then beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Fry as you would pancakes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and top with bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers.
Put butter on bake and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: carrot-apple cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch tube pan. In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add applesauce and oil. Stir until blended. Add eggs and stir. When batter is smooth, add carrots and mix well. Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Stir all and put into a 9 or 10-inch pie crust.
Beat 3 eggs and 1 cup milk and pour over pie.
Prepare a lattice top crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macadamia cheese hors d'ouevres
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, cut butter into biscuit mix until coarse crumbs. Stir in egg, nuts, cheese and pepper. Mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes. Makes 48 pieces.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mash potato chunks in soup first, then add soup.
Add half and half and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add crabmeat and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Roll mixture into a long roll and roll in pecans and parsley flakes.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Ground turkey can be used instead of sausage.
Brown sausage or turkey.
Cut zucchini into bite size pieces.
Place all ingredients into soup pot.
Add water and cook until vegetables are done.

title: punch(two gallons)
directions: One gallon equals 36 cups.

title: peas with vegetable sauce
directions: Cook peas and drain.
Combine all ingredients and mix with peas.
Refrigerate.

title: mincemeat fruit cake
directions: Cook mincemeat in water for 1 minute.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour mincemeat mixture over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan. Bake at 250° for about an hour or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon and remove waste and bones.
Crumble into a bowl. Add beaten raw egg, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Shape into salmon croquettes and roll into corn meal to coat completely.
Fry in preheated cooking oil until lightly browned on all sides.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add soda and salt.
Sift together 3 times.
Cream Crisco thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Melt chocolate and blend into egg mixture. Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° to 375°.
Cool and frost with White Icing.

title: chocolate clair
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to the box directions.
Add Cool Whip; stir until well blended. Layer in a 13 x 9 pan with graham crackers, 1/2 of the pudding and graham crackers. Spread chocolate frosting on graham crackers.
Add other half of pudding, layer of graham crackers and spread with frosting.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine; season with salt and pepper. Remove chicken and in same pan, saute onions.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, arrange chicken and top with onions and 1/2 jar salsa.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add rest of salsa; dollop sour cream and cheese and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: our lord's scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together to create this divine fruitcake. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May the richness of God's blessings fill your heart.

title: baked potato and onions
directions: Make slits 1 1/2-inches apart in baked potato.
Do not slice all the way through potato.
Place a slice of Vidalia onion in each slit.
Wrap in foil.
Bake.

title: finger-lickin' snack mix
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Divide between two (9 x 13-inch) cake pans.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture, gently coating evenly.
Bake at 250° about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown. Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 15 or 20 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out dry.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Mix with spinach, cottage cheese and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: country style steak
directions: Roll steak in seasoned flour and brown on each side in margarine.
Put in Dutch oven and cover with water.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, or until meat is tender and gravy is thickened. Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water in large pot.
Season with salt and celery seed.
Cook until potatoes and onions are tender.

title: microwave tacos
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chopped onion, chopped green pepper and minced garlic.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, or until beef is browned, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and microwave at High 3 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons meat mixture into each taco shell.
Top meat with lettuce, chopped tomato, cheese and taco sauce.
Serve immediately.
Yields 12 servings.

title: garlic spinach dip
directions: Cook in saucepan spinach according to package directions; drain.
Place garlic in blender.
Add cooked spinach, milk, salt and pepper sauce.
Add cheese.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter on stove and stir in brown sugar.
Cook for few seconds.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; serve.

title: snack cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well, then stir in cereals.
